name: Stone's throw from Albert Cuypmarkt
space: Located in “De Pijp” neighborhood, the bustling and lively heart of Amsterdam, is our beautiful and spacious, 130 square-meter, two-level apartment: “Casa Soufflé”. De Pijp is perfectly situated just far enough away from the center to be free of traffic and crowds, but close enough to get to anywhere in Amsterdam you’d want to go very easily – either by foot or tram. De Pijp feels very authentically local – so you really get to feel like you’re living like the Amsterdammers do! Casa Soufflé is just two streets away from Amsterdam’s famous Albert Cuyp street market where you can pick up delicious meat, fish, cheese, nuts and produce, snack on some loempia, or just wander around and take in all the different stalls have to offer. We are just one block from beautiful Sarphatipark and de Pijp’s vibrant local bars, cafés, and restaurants. We are just a 7-minute (600 meter) walk to the Heineken Experience, and only a 12-15 minute (1 km) walk to Museumplein where you can spend the day taking

We love living in Amsterdam and will happily help advise places to go, places to eat and drink, and things to see and do – and may even join. :)

name: Cosy apartment close to (Wester) park and centre
summary: Bohemian apartment (60m2) in Amsterdam - west (next to the beautiful Westerpark which offers plenty of cultural sides, 20 min walking from the heart of Amsterdam - including central station - and 10 min from the popular Jordaan area). Don't feel like walking? There are busses and trams leaving around the corner, also to central station.  No loud noise after 10 Pm due to neighbours.  Last but not least; a very lovely and accessible place to stay with a sunny balcony :)

name: Spacious Apartment close to centre and Vondelpark
summary: Comfortable apartment close to the Vondelpark. We have a completely renovated kitchen and bathroom alongside a spacious living room. There are two balconies and a canal view from the living room. There is a bicycle rent around the corner so you can cycle to the center in 10 minutes. Also, it is very easy to get around with public transport from and to our home. We are there to make you feel welcome and to tell you about the best places to go. We are happy to welcome you :). Mark & Claudia

name: Canal house+VIEW | City Center | Jordaan | Terrace
summary: If you want to spend your Amsterdam city trip in the best way possible, then look no further.  This amazing, luxurious apartment is situated at one of the prettiest canals, right in the heart of our beatiful capital Amsterdam.
space: The apartment is very spacious and perfect for e.g. a romantic getaway with your loved one. The living area is gorgeously decorated with a nice mix of modern and antique interior and looks like a showroom right out of a prestigious catalog. The kitchen is state-of-the-art and fully equipped with everything you need to prepare a nice meal for you and your travel party. There are two lovely bedrooms fitted with comfortable double beds, which makes you want to snooze just a little longer in the mornings.  If you feel like waking up in the morning sun with a cup of coffee, you can do that on our private balcony/rooftop terrace connected to the bedroom. APARTMENT HIGHLIGHTS:  ★ Location, Location & Location close to all highlights! ★ Canal View ★ Private balcony / Roof terrace ★ Spacious living area with Stylish interior ★ Fully Equipped kitchen ★ FREE & FAST WIFI and TV

neighborhood_overview: De Jordaan in Amsterdam is known for its cozy atmosphere. We love to walk around the tiny little streets and canals, and discover new restaurants and authentic cafés. In this neighbourhood you can find a mix of artists, students and young entrepreneurs, but also the ‘original Amsterdammers’. All Major sights (e.g. Dam Square,...) are within walking distance!
notes: We will welcome you into a warm and clean home. For your comfort, we will provide you with freshly made up beds and towels upon arrival.
transit: Public transport is everywhere. Easy access from Schiphol and Amsterdam Central station. Private parking facilities at walking distance. As this is the perfect base for exploring the city, you won't really need any public transport to see the major sights in Amsterdam. But please contact us if you need any information, We will give you customized guidance and tips on thebest ways to travel.
access: You will have access to the entire apartment and rooftop terrace, a place to call your own during your stay. Please make yourself at home! Please contact us to inform about our flexible check-in & check-out times.
interaction: Please feel free to contact us before and during your stay. We will be happy to answer all your questions. We will personally be present for your check-in to welcome you, hand over the keys and show you around. We are always on standby for any questions or remarks, furthermore we respect your privacy and only interact if requested or required. We know our city very well, and we would love to help you out with recommendations and getting around the city.
house_rules: A lot of effort has been put in the apartment to make this a nice, peaceful, clean and tidy place. We expect our guests to treat the apartment in the same respectful way as we do. Therefore, we kindly ask you to respect, and agree on the following house rules: • No additional guests, or visitors are allowed without our approval. • Quiet hours are between 10 pm – 8 am. On the terrace between 8 pm - 8 am. • Be considerate of the neighbors at all times. • House parties are strictly prohibited. • Smoking and/or drug use is not allowed inside the apartment. • We don’t allow third party bookings, without consulting us upfront. • In your first airbnb message, please tell us what your favorite color is (just to ensure us that you actually read the house rules ;))  We want to be as transparent as possible about the apartment and the details of your stay. name: Bright, Spacious & Trendy close to Vondelpark!
summary: Welcome to my home! It's bright & spacious in a trendy, yet cozy manner. The location is great! In a hip area called ""Old West"" very close to theVondelpark & city centre but quiet & with a lot of shops, trendy bars & restaurants. Please check my travel guide for tips on where to go. Several supermarkets within walking distance and the Overtoom; a long street with a lot of trendy stores and public transport which will take you into the centre or to Schiphol airport very quickly. Welcome!
space: The apartment is located on the second floor with an open plan fully equipped kitchen, bathroom and bedroom with comfortable double sized bed. I'll make sure that you have fresh linnen and towels and storage for your clothes.

neighborhood_overview: The neighborhood is a quiet area where both young families and young professionals live.  There are many nice cafes, restaurants and trendy bars within walking distance. A nice brunch place which is around the corner is called ""Staring at Jacob"" and a nice bar close by is called ""Cafe Lennep"" and ""Panache"". However, there are many other nice places, for example the on J.P. Heijestraat, Overtoom and Kinkerstraat. The Vondelpark is very close by for a morning walk. The foodhallen (which also includes a cinema) is an indoor food market and a great way to taste many different types of food in one evening.
transit: Tram 1 which goes to the central station stops very close by. The stop is called 'Rhijnvis Feithstraat', on the Overtoom. The same tram (in the other direction) goes to station Lelylaan, which is 10min from Schiphol airport. Two other tram stops that are very close by are tram 7 and 17, which leave from Kinkerstraat.
access: There are no shared areas except for the staircase. You will have the house to yourself. Please be quiet on the shared staircase and kind to my neighbors. Thank you!
interaction: If I'm not able to welcome you myself I will make sure someone will be there to welcome you, show you around and answer all your questions.

name: City centre, cozy room for solo traveller
summary: Central location, perfect to explore the city on foot. Most highlights are within  walking distance: main canals, Museum Quarter, Nine Streets, Red Light District, Vondelpark, Food-/Filmhallen, art galleries, coffee shops and Leiden Square (Leidseplein) entertainment area. Room is on first floor in modern apartmentbuilding with elevator, at a quiet, old canal in the popular, lively Jordaan area. This is a straight-friendly and gay-friendly place where you can feel free and welcome.
space: Cozy, 6 m2 small room with big doublebed. Room has direct access to adjacent north-west directed 3 m2 balcony looking on quiet inner court.

neighborhood_overview: The 17th century Jordaan area is popular and lively. Near by are supermarkets and all kinds of little restaurants in different priceranges, some take-away also, as well as some snackbars and coffeeshops. Main canal-area and old centre are near by.  Well known Nine Streets shopping area and Prinsengracht with its Anne Frank House, houseboats and houseboatmuseum are only about 150 meters away. Even closer there is a fitness centre. Also close by are the Food-/Filmhallen. The OBA hotspot in the public library in these Hallen  gives via Pressreader online access to countless international newspapers.
notes: Smoking is possible on both balconies.  In the kitchen you can use the refrigerator, microwave, water-heater, coffeemachine and - on request - kitchen utensils. Free, unlimited make-it-yourself coffee and tea. Use of washing machine on request. You provide your own breakfast, which is easy because there are two supermarkets and several breakfastplaces near by. Sometimes your host is looking after a friend's dog.
transit: Several tram- and busstops are near by. Central train station is only 5 tramstops away. Busstop of bus to/from airport  only five minutes on foot. Carpark near by, but budgetwise is P+R, in combination with public transport, a better deal.

interaction: Your host will be happy to give you additional advice if needed.

name: Thailand apartment Amsterdam
summary: Compact and comfortable one-bedroom apartment for up to four guests, in the trendy and upcoming West area of Amsterdam.
space: This comfortable accommodation, with an Asian touch, wooden floors and large windows that allow in plenty of natural light, is perfect for two couples or a family. The bright and cheerful living area has a large sofa (converts into a double bed),  a flat screen television with cable and a dining table for four. The separate kitchen is well equipped, and includes an oven, microwave, fridge and freezer.  The bedroom has a comfortable double bed. The bathroom is modern and features a toilet, washbasin and shower. This apartment has everything you need for a stay in Amsterdam.  Located close to the Erasmus park and easy reachable by public transport, makes this a perfect base from which to explore the city. Breakfast can be requested when booking (€ 15,- per person per day). The host will provide a refrigerator stocked with bread, milk, cheese, eggs, meats and juice.

neighborhood_overview: This apartment is situated in the West of the City, and is close to all the amenities you may need. Want a bite to eat? Restaurants and cafés are plentiful, and for those who prefer cooking at home – there are plenty of shops in the neighbourhood too.  If relaxation is your thing, then the Erasmus Park is a stone’s throw away, or take a walk to the famous Vondel Park. If you like  shopping, a short tram ride will take you to the heart of Amsterdam’s most exclusive shopping street, the PC Hooftstraat, with designer shops galore.
transit: The Palace on Dam Square and the hectic Kalverstraat shopping street are all only a cycle or tram ride away. Visit the tempting Lindengracht food market on a Saturday morning, or the farmers' market on the Noordermarkt. Just half an hour away is the Museumplein, home to the Van Gogh Museum, the newly reopened Stedelijk Museum of Modern Art and the Rijksmuseum with its collection of world renowned masterworks.  Something for every taste! The apartment is well situated for getting around Amsterdam. Central Station is just a short tram ride away.
house_rules: Drugs are strictly prohibited in our apartment. Check-in is from 14:00 to 20:00 Early check-in depending on the availability for €30 Late check-in is €50 Late check-out depends on the availability is €50

name: Fantastic apartment with balcony in Amsterdam
summary: Welcome to our lovely, light and spacious two-floor apartment of 100m2, close to the vibrant and exciting centre of Amsterdam! It has all the stores close to the house to give you a great stay. such as the supermarket etc.  In only 15 minutes you're in the city centre by public transport, you just have to take the tram around the corner of our house.  We hope you enjoy your stay here in our great apartment and in the wonderful city of Amsterdam!
space: When you reach the second floor you'll enter our beautiful design kitchen area with a steam oven, Nespresso machine for your great cup of coffee in the morning and a large fridge for your cold beer and wine, which you'll enjoy on the magnificent roof terrace!  In the nice and light living you can relax and watch some TV, listen to the SONOS system or dine together with your friends or family.  There's one bedroom on the second floor, which has doors to the balcony, so once you wake up, open the doors and enjoy your morning with the sounds of various species of birds!  The bathroom is situated on the second floor and has a New York subway-style design. There's a washing machine and dryer too.  On the third floor you find the master bedroom, including the walk-in closet. Also on this floor you have access our superb roof terrace, from where you enjoy your evening. If you don't feel like going out for dinner, make use of our Weber bbq and enjoy the sunset with a nice cold beverage!
description: Welcome to our lovely, light and spacious two-floor apartment of 100m2, close to the vibrant and exciting centre of Amsterdam! It has all the stores close to the house to give you a great stay. such as the supermarket etc.  In only 15 minutes you're in the city centre by public transport, you just have to take the tram around the corner of our house.  We hope you enjoy your stay here in our great apartment and in the wonderful city of Amsterdam! When you reach the second floor you'll enter our beautiful design kitchen area with a steam oven, Nespresso machine for your great cup of coffee in the morning and a large fridge for your cold beer and wine, which you'll enjoy on the magnificent roof terrace!  In the nice and light living you can relax and watch some TV, listen to the SONOS system or dine together with your friends or family.  There's one bedroom on the second floor, which has doors to the balcony, so once you wake up, open the doors and enjoy your morning with the sounds of va
neighborhood_overview: The Hoofddorpplein (Hoofddorp square) neighborhood is very quiet and and is very close to the beautiful Vondelpark where you can stroll around and enjoy the beauty of it!  In close proximity of our apartment you find various shops (Hoofddorp square) and supermarkets. Great bars and restaurants are at walking distance. A bit further you find on the Amstelveenseweg numerous other bars and restaurants.
notes: Be respectfull to the neighbours.
transit: Public transportation brings you in 15 minutes to the city centre, there are various trams and buses going in that direction.  Train station Amsterdam Lelylaan is at 15 minute walking distance from the apartment and from there you reach Schiphol Airport in 8 minutes and costs you only a few euros to get there.
access: You can use the entire apartment.
house_rules: - Please respect our neighbors at all times. The roof terrace is ideal for your relaxing evening, but keep in mind that our neighbors also enjoy their evening.  - Please don't make use of the roof terrace after 10pm.  - Please do not smoke inside the house and stair case. On the roof terrace this is not a problem, as long as the cigaret butts are not thrown down or left behind on the terrace. Keep the terrace clean and tidy. - Please don't bring your pet. - Please don't give any parties or events, remember to respect the neighbors. - Please do not use any drugs in or around the premises. This means the roof terrace and balcony as well!

There is an outdoor playground across the street where you can play soccer, tennis and skateboard. Different kind of shops are at 200m from the apartment with a quality bakery, cheese and wine shop and an organic supermarket (Marqt) is at 250 m. There are nice restaurants with good food close by. They are showed on the map. The centre is 10-15 min by bike and public transfer is at 200m from the apartment. Here you have tramline number 24 which takes you to the museumsquare in 10-15 minutes! There is a place around the corner of the apartment where you can rent bikes, it's called 'Parnassus bike's'.

Experience the best of both worlds: a quiet neighborhood but with easy access to the city centre and public transport. Take an easy stroll along the river to reach the centre in 10 mins, or take the metro that is just around the corner. Supermarket nearby and plenty of restaurants in the neighborhood.

Here you will find the master bedroom (kingsize boxspring 180x200cm), second bedroom (140x190cm) with balcony and garden view, and the bathroom with bathtub and rain shower. summary: Very beautiful, 17th century, charming, sunny and quiet and semi-free standing house in the center of Amsterdam (Jordaan), with a balcony and a terrace. Close to Noordermarkt, shops, cafe's and restaurants. Maximum 4 persons. Max six when one family.
space: The house is spacious with a big living room with design furniture and an open kitchen. The kitchen has all the facilities you'll need, like a dishwasher, fridge, espresso machine etc. At the backside of the house there is a private terrace where you can enjoy the peacefulness and the sun. A peaceful master bedroom (with kingsize bed) is located on the first floor. Next to this room is the bathroom with bath tub, separate douche and toilet.  The balcony can be entered from the master bedroom. On the second floor you'll find two bedrooms with in each room a single bed and a sofa bed for two persons. Next to these rooms is a toilet and a little bathroom with shower and sink. On the top floor you'll find the washing machine and dryer.

neighborhood_overview: The house is located walking/cycling distance from everything you want to see! The canals, 'the Nine Streets' (very popular shopping area), Red Light District, musea, Anne Frank house, flower market, the Royal Palace, galleries, bars, cafe's, restaurants. The house is located in 'the Jordaan', the creative centre of Amsterdam. The supermarkets are 1 minute away. The famous Saturday (bio) markets and the Monday flee market are around the corner. You can make a canal boat trip during the day and night and enjoy the amazing 16th century architecture of Amsterdam. You can easily visit the trendy upcoming 'North' (with a free ferry ride leaving from central station), where you will find the new 'EYE' filmmuseum.
transit: The house is at 10 min walking distance from Central Station and 5 minutes away from tramline number 3, which brings you f.e. to the museum district. The ferry to the North part of Amsterdam is also at walking distance (10 min). Bicycles can be rented around the corner.
access: You can use the entire house, except two little storage rooms on the top floor.
interaction: You can contact me by phone. My father, who lives closeby, will do the check ins and outs and is always available for any questions.

We have 2 adult bikes and 2 children's bikes (22 inches and 26 inches). More or other bikes can easily be rented nearby.

Het lijkt alsof we in een dorpje in de grote stad wonen, waar je de drukte op kan zoeken door het IJ over te steken, maar ook kan ontvluchten door weer naar huis te gaan. Het is een erg fijne plek om te wonen.

neighborhood_overview: Top location! The hidden gem of Amsterdam. We live at the Sloterplas ('plas' means lake) in the Sloterpark. Next to the beach (swimming water!) with a harbour where you can rent boats, canoes, surfboards etc.  A stroll around the lake is 6 km and gives you great views, you can also cycle around it.  Lot's of facilities for sports, playgrounds, swimmingpool, beach picknicks and bbq in the park etc. Our house is at the lakeside (comes with a view) in a quiet residential area.  This al in just 15 minutes from downtown Amsterdam :) Staying here gives you the opportunity to experience the best of both worlds.
notes: We've got 2 lovely cats, we leave them at home giving you the upportunity to cuddle and play with them. So it helps if you are a bit of a cat lover.

neighborhood_overview: The studio is located perfectly in vibrant area 'De Pijp'. On the left is the romantic Sarphatipark, with in its 'Liefdesbruggetje' (lovers bridge).  Since 1880 lovers would show each other, and the neighbourhood, that they are an item. To the right is the Albert Cuyp market, Hollands longest market. 'De Pijp' is without doubt a melting pot of cultures and nationalities. It is brimming with fantastic cafés, culinary restaurants, coffee shops, supermarkets and bars. A heaven for foodies! The nearest supermarket, Albert Heijn, is a 2 minute walk. Within walking distance from the studio you will find popular sites such as the Heineken Museum, the Van Gogh Museum, The Stedelijk museum, Vondelpark, The Royal Concert hall, Paradiso, Leidseplein and the Rijksmuseum.  There is also a canal cruise dock opposite the Heineken Museum. The city center is a 15 minute walk away. The studio is also close to RAI conference center. name: Sunny apartment with beautiful canalview
summary: A spacious and comfortable, in 2014 completely renovated, apartment on the first floor of a traditional Amsterdam house from 1914. The apartment has a  canal view and you are right around the corner of Vondelpark.
space: This apartment, a spacious, in 2014 completely renovated house on the first floor of a typical Amsterdam house is perfectly suitable for someone traveling by themself or a couple who wants to enjoy Amsterdam.  The L shaped living room (40m2 ) is located at the front of the apartment. The living room contains six large windows through which the sunlight comes through all day.  From the balcony, at the front of the house, you can enjoy the Amsterdam city life: bicycles , trams, boats and sun are passing all day long. The open kitchen in the living room is equipped with comfort, including a Quoocker (boiling water tap), dishwasher, and microwave-oven . There is a large modern bathroom with floor heating, bath and separate rain shower. The bedroom is next to the bathroom at the site of the courtyard, making it a quiet place to sleep.

neighborhood_overview: The apartment is located in the neighborhood Oud West at the corner of Oud Zuid. Oud West is known for the nice (coffee) bars, restaurants and concept-stores, which makes it more of a less touristy spot to stay.  Oud Zuid represents more of the posh Amsterdam.  Within two minutes’ walk you are in the Vondelpark. Through the Vondelpark you can walk/cycle to the Museumplein with the Van Gogh, Stedelijk and Rijksmuseum.
transit: The apartment is 10 minutes by car or train from Schiphol Airport.  In front of the house is a tramstop (tram 1) which brings you to the Leidse Square (5 minutes) or Amsterdam central station (15 minutes). Car parking at the apartment is public and 4 EUR per hour. But the best way to explore Amsterdam is by foot, bike or boat of course!!!
access: You will have the whole apartment to yourself.

neighborhood_overview: The famous ‘’De Pijp’’ is one of the most cosmopolitan and vibrant neighborhoods in the South of Amsterdam, but it is close to the City Centre. Formerly it was a working class quarter. It is a very diverse neighborhood with more then 100 different nationalities. The van Woustraat is one of the commercial streets of this district, with many different restaurants, bars and shops. These streets are always busy, but through the whole district you will find coffee shops and a lot of different ethnic food. You cannot visit the de Pijp without visiting the Albert Cuyp market, here you will find more than 100 shops. It is a real Dutch market with many stalls with vegetables, cheese, fish and clothes. The Sarphatipark is located in this district, it is a beautiful urban park. You can escape the busy city and go for a nice walk. The famous Heineken Experience is also located in this district. 'De Pijp' is without doubt a melting pot of cultures and nationalities. It is brimming with fantastic cafés, culinary restaurants, coffee shops, supermarkets and bars. A heaven for foodies! The nearest supermarket, Albert Heijn, is a 2 minute walk. Within walking distance from the studio you will find popular sites such as the Heineken Museum, the Van Gogh Museum, The Stedelijk museum, Vondelpark, The Royal Concert hall, Paradiso, Leidseplein and the Rijksmuseum. neighborhood_overview: Only a short walk form the main party square in Amsterdam, Leidseplein. Leidseplein is located in the heart of Amsterdam. This well-connected area started in the 17th century as a parking place for farmers’ horses and carts. Today, the busy square is one of the city’s most popular nightlife areas, home to famous music venues, fun dance clubs, relaxed bars and more. Leidseplein is a great area to book your accommodation here in Amsterdam, as it’s centrally located. Leidseplein is a transportation hub, where several bus and tram lines meet, and within walking distance of many major Amsterdam attractions, such as the Rijksmuseum and floating flower market. Surrounding the square, you’ll find a variety of restaurants and a vibrant nightlife scene. 2 of the top night clubs are 15 minute walk form my house, Melkweg and Pardiso.
notes: We have a lovely kitten in the house, she’s very nice and playful. In line with this, I ask you to please always close the front and back doors so she won't get lost outside the house. If you have a large group coming to Amsterdam, I can arrange extra beds and blankets for extra guests.  I have a full detailed guidebook in the apartment waiting for you. This contains hundreds of my personal recommendations of things to do, things to see, places to eat, places to drink. Along with all this information I have provided plenty of maps and tourism brochures for a lot of the main tourist attractions in the city. Also contains a small piece about the history of Amsterdam and The Netherlands. I have also wrote out a list of the 20 best things to do while in Amsterdam city. Enjoy :)
transit: The house is about 20 minutes from central station.The number 24 tram will leave you a 2 minute walk form the apartment. The house is very central, so you will save a lot of money on public transport because you can walk to all the main tourist attractions from out home.The house is close to the Albert Cuypstraat market. This market is really cool and one of the top to see spots for people visiting the city.

name: Your own Romantic Private Boat for 2!
summary: Asile Flottant is a collection of characteristic hotel boats docked in the shallow waters of a creative hotspot just minutes from the historic city center. One of our traditional ships could be your private floating hotel room while visiting Amsterdam. Just picture yourself gazing at the horizon from your own wheelhouse or having a locally brewed beer on the sundeck before dozing off in your vintage cabin. Sounds like quite a journey, right?
space: If there would be an Oscar for Best Floating Love Nest our Anneliese would definitely be doing a yearly thank-you-speech for the decades to come. Trust us, if you’re looking for something extraordinary for just the two of you, look no further. First of all, there’s the exterior. Between all the industrial steel and rough concrete, the pointy baby-blue derrière of Anneliese truly sticks out. Once below deck you step into your own romantic bubble. Your double bed is located in the spacious and clear white wooden forepeak with natural skylight, while in the bathtub you look straight into the massive engine room. We can go on forever, but no one can convince you better than Anneliese herself. She’s waiting for you. Year: 1934 Type: Cutter Size: 18×5 meters Max. Guests: 2 Bathrooms: 1 Bedrooms: 1 Bed * One king-size double bed (180 x 200 cm) in the forepeak

neighborhood_overview: We are located in the quiet waters of a former shipyard just north of the historic city center of Amsterdam. This former industrial plot, also known as De Ceuvel, has been converted into one of the most unique and sustainable urban developments in Europe. The outcome is truly mind-blowing. Old houseboats have been hoisted on land and the jetty connecting the vessels isn’t hanging over water but over a green ocean of soil-cleaning plants. Each boat houses creative and social startups or artists showing a true entrepreneurial and sustainable spirit. While the jetty offers some seriously great spots to unwind, café De Ceuvel attracts the biggest crowds. On hot summer days (yes, we do have those) the terrace transforms into a lively festival-like wharf making it hard to believe the city center is just a 5-minute bike ride away. On the edge of the terrace you’ll find our private pier leading to the remains of the piled fendering and the boat lifts that were designed and constructed in the 1
notes: Limited free parking! Please note that it is not possible to sail with this ship.
transit: There’s roughly four ways to get to us: by foot or by (rental) bike, with your own (rental) car or by taxi, by public transportation or by boat. We’ll discuss the first three. Once you arranged your own boat to get around town, which quite frankly is not a bad thought, we’ll talk again. From the airport (Schiphol) The airport is not far from the city center. By taxi it takes approx. 30 minutes to get to Asile Flottant, but quite a bit longer during rush hours. The cost of a taxi from the airport will be around 70 euros. The train is a lot cheaper and quite convenient since the airport houses a railway station with direct links to the Central Railway Station (approx. 15 minutes/ 5 euros one way). From there you can either continue by foot or by bus. By foot or by bike Do as the Romans do and hop on a (rental) bike. Pouring rain, blizzards or a heatwave; the Dutch bicycle 365 days per year and that’s not without a reason. The city of Amsterdam is extremely bike friendly and rather car-un
access: Acces to the whole boat for yourself! Includes Towels & Linen, Hair & Body Products, Coffee & Tea (limited), Kitchenette (Cooking not possible!)
interaction: We would be delighted to host you throughout your entire stay. Feel free to contact us if you have any questions or need anything in the boat.
house_rules: We expect you to respect the property as if it were your own Be considerate about our valuables and your surroundings! Please do not flush anything down the toilet unless you have eaten it first Seriously, only use the toilets for toilet tissue and dispose of other products in the little bin next to the toilet. The boats use special grinder pumps which are very, very expensive. If they have to be repaired (because you decided to enrich their diet with condoms, cleaning wipes or other products), we’ll be forced to charge you for it! If you want to smoke, please go outside We don’t want our boats to smell like an ashtray! Safety regulations also forbid it. In fact, any kind of open fire (that includes barbecues, unless we’re throwing you a party) is prohibited. No loud noises after 22.00 Please be respectful of your neighbours!
host_about:
We will be the sincere smiles you meet upon arrival and we are the ones on the other side of the screen whenyou’re behind your computer organizing your trip: we are Irene, David, Esther, Huib, Sam, and Feikje. And together we are 'Team Asile'. The moment we got to know of Asile Flottant it was love at first sight and we truly feel privileged being part of such a unique, sustainable and once-in- a-lifetime project. The fleet feels like a small herd to us; we truly care about each ship and we can’t really say which is our favorite. The vessels have so much character and style, all in their own beautiful way, that we just got equally attached to all of them. We all have our own role at Asile Flottant. David is the one you probably have contact with when you prepare for your trip. He is our 'back-office' hero and he makes sure all the paperwork is in order. Irene is our senior host. She invented ""service with a smile"" and if you are lucky she will be the one to check you in upon arrival. Also Irene is the girl to contact whenever you want to organize something special to make your trip even better! Esther and Feikje are also hosts of Asile Flottant and also very happy to welcome you. Last but not least there are Huib and Sam, They are our technical engineers and they can fix/build/repare (almost) anything! 

The best thing about our work? Okay, this sounds like an advertising-answer, but honestly: it’s you! Having you here with us to see how you fall in love with your ship, with De Ceuvel and with our city fills us with joy. Actually, it’s the best energizer ever! If you have any questions please drop us a line. We’d be more than happy to answer any question you might have. Even better: we’d love to welcome you on our pier one day soon. We’re looking
forward!

The apartment is close to the Javastreet .The Javastraat is a long street with many nice coffee boutiques,  good restaurants, bars,  shops and grocery stores. The apartment is also nearby the Amsterdam University and the College at the sciencepark.

neighborhood_overview: This classy apartment is located in the popular Amsterdam-Zuid, Amsterdam South, neighborhood. The neighborhood is well known for its special architecture, called 'Plan Berlage', and it's high quality of living. There are supermarkets and shops close by and you will find various restaurants and bars within walking distance. You can easily walk or take a bike to the 'hip and happening' De Pijp-area and the Amsterdam city center with it's beautiful canals. You will have the best of both worlds as you will stay in a quiet neighborhood and at the same time you are close to all the excitement you could wish for. The South neighborhood is very well connected to all other parts of Amsterdam. It is easy to get a bus, tram or metro which will bring you virtually anywhere.

neighborhood_overview: Nestled between de Pijp and the river Amstel, the Rivierenbuurt is a quiet, residential neighbourhood remarkable for the fact that it’s managed to keep its architectural plan exactly as it was built and envisioned in the 30s (it is a famous example of the Amsterdam School of which HP Berlage was chief architect). Its roads (such as the Scheldestraat) leading out of town are packed with speciality restaurants, but for the rest, this is more of a stay home neighbourhood than going out (but when you do, you’re only about a 10 minute bike to the bright lights!)
notes: Freshly made up beds and crispy towels (one per person) will be waiting for you upon arrival.
transit: My advice is to rent a bike. The 15 minute bike ride to the city centre is surely worth it! You can also take Tram number 4 to and from central station/city centre. Get off at tramstop Amstelkade, this is almost next to the front door!

host_about:
Hi,

My name is Leanne and I have been a proud inhabitant of the great city of Amsterdam for almost seven years. I love to travel, and when I go I love to stay at peoples homes!

The houses tell a story and are unique instead of cold and massive hotels.

My home is one of my prides! Everything you want to see in Amsterdam is in walking or biking distance.

I am currently starting up my own business in Amsterdam and in order to help me get started I rent out my house and make sure people get to see the real local Amsterdam.

Great cafe tips and of course some local food will be waiting for you. 

Optional a private boat tour can be booked, with me as your captain!

neighborhood_overview: Our house is located in ""De Pijp"", one of the most popular neighborhoods of Amsterdam – cozy but yet cosmopolitan, trendy and diverse. This artistic area is full of fantastic cafés, lunchrooms, local special beer breweries and (wine)bars. Shopping is also great in the small boutique stores all around us. In the middle of trendy De Pijp area is one of the nicest parks in Amsterdam –Sarphatipark. The nation’s most famous outdoor market: is here - Albert Cuypmarkt. It attracts thousands of visitors every day, and with over 300 stalls you can find there anything - food, flowers, clothes, furniture, art... Heineken brewery (Heineken Experience) is here as well. Heineken's rich and successful history has been presented in their old defunct brewery with several amusement park attractions added to the exhibit. You are just 5 min. away from Amsterdam's finest arts - the Rijksmuseum, van Gogh and the Stedelijk museum at Museum square, as well as the famous Concertgebouw concert hall. The RAI Con

neighborhood_overview: The Haarlemmerstraat and -dijk were declared the nicest shopping street in the Netherlands in 2011. Both streets together form a true gem located in the historical Jordaan area. The local residents consider it a small and cozy village, where everyone knows everyone. You will find all kinds of shops ranging from independent boutiques, specialized shops and small salons to trendy but affordable restaurants and bars and even the oldest cinema in Amsterdam, called the Movies. Famous buildings on the Haarlemmerstraat include the West Indisch Huis, where in 1625 the Dutch West India Company's governors ordered the construction of a fort on the island of Manhattan, laying the foundations for New York City. In short, this trendy and quirky street is perfect for spending hours roaming, shopping and dining. The shopping night falls on Thursday with stores open until 9:00 pm.

neighborhood_overview: Amsterdam West is one of the most diverse neighbourhoods in town. You find almost everything there! You will find a diversity of hipster- proof coffee places, cool concept stores and vintage boutiques. Amsterdam West is also great for foodies! You find a nice eatery at almost every corner.

The cosy atmosphere will make you feel right at home after a long day of exploring the city.

neighborhood_overview: The City Center is close! The Amsterdam Amstel train station is on a five minute walk. The metro and trains take you to the city center in an eight minutes and depart every five to ten minutes By bike it takes about 15 minutes to the city center; take the ‘Wibautstraat’. Amsterdam East is a lively neighbourhood, with some of the newest bars and restaurants and the famous international ‘Dappermarket’ nearby, as well as the famous Zoo ‘Artis’.
notes: Please note that there is no check-in desk. The check-in will be personally done by the host at the hotel itself in the  Ringdijk 58 Amsterdam. Our check-in time is between 2PM and 8PM. A late check-in after 8PM comes with an additional charge of 30EUR.
transit: From there Central Station it is very easy to get to the hotel. From the station you will have to take the metro  51/53/54 towards the Amstel Station, from there it is just a 5 minute walk to the hotel. Otherwise, the taxi (TCA) or Uber are also good options!
access: Accompanied to the hotel, you will find our restaurant De Vergulden Eenhoorn, an oasis of tranquillity. Here you can have a wonderful homemade breakfast, lunch or dinner made with locally sourced products.
interaction: During the day there will be a host available. The host is there to help with any questions and or suggestions.

host_about: Capital Apartments is a young and fast growing rental agency which is specialized in short- and medium stay apartment rentals. Whether you are traveling for business or leisure we want to make sure that you can enjoy the freedom and comfort of your own exclusive and fully equipped apartment. We are a young and dynamic team driven by our passion for hospitality and creating a “home away from home” for our guests. name: Cosy and comfortable in the center of Amsterdam
summary: A recently-redecorated, charming, light and spacious two-bedroom apartment in the central Amsterdam area called 'De Plantagebuurt' (The Plantation neighborhood). The apartment is located in one of the most beautiful streets of Amsterdam and has everything you’ll need for a wonderful stay. Besides Artis, which is across the street, there are many museums, shops, markets and restaurants in the neighborhood. One hotspot you should not miss is restaurant De Plantage at the end of the street.
space: The apartment is completely redecorated with both new and antique furniture and we supplied new bed linen, pillows and towels. Because of the big windows it is a very bright apartment. It has a fully-operational kitchen with dishwasher, oven, microwave and washing machine. It has two bedrooms, one with a double bed and one with two single beds attached to each other. There is a one-person sofabed in the living room. It has a bathroom with a shower and a separate toilet. In the living room there is a small balcony from which you can see the zoo. Sometimes you hear the roar of a lion or the song of the gibbons. The apartment is on the second floor of a beautiful 19th century building, located in a street so beautiful, it is often seen in Dutch movies.  We are proud to share the result with the Airb&b community. Be welcome, cold beers and bubbles are in the fridge!

neighborhood_overview: The apartment is located in the center of Amsterdam in an area called ‘De Plantagebuurt’ (The Plantation neighborhood). The street itself is very calm. Besides Artis, which is across the street, and the nearby Hortus Botanicus there are a lot of museums in the neighborhood such as Rembrandthuis (the house of Rembrandt),  Hermitage Amsterdam, Verzetsmuseum Amsterdam (the Dutch Resistance Museum), Tropenmuseum, Nemo (science museum) and Het Scheepvaartmuseum (The National Maritime Museum). There are many nice hotspots around our house, like cozy Café Koosje or picturesque De Plantage.
transit: Within a two-minute walk there is a tram station with several lines (9 and 14) connected to it. There is also a metro station within a five-minute walk. It brings you to Central Station in five minutes. Of course, the fastest, healthiest and most fun way to travel through Amsterdam is by bike. There is a bike rental around the corner. Due to the central location of the apartment you will most likely be able to get to all the hotspots in just 20 minutes by bike.
access: The entire apartment is exclusively for the guests.
interaction: Our son lives on the third floor of the same building and will be available for any questions you may have. He will most likely be the one to welcome you on your arrival to the apartment.
host_about: I have a husband and 3 kids. As an air hostess for KLM I have seen a lot of the world but I could never stay for very long in one place. Now, since my kids are grown up, I have the time to make longer trips. So either you are lucky to be able to stay in my beautiful apartment in Amsterdam or I am lucky to stay in your place somewhere else in the world!

neighborhood_overview: The modest origins of the Jordaan (it was built to house Jewish and French immigrant workers) is still visible in its small, very old houses and the fact there is an old cafe on nearly every corner (often the type where locals will burst into folk music on Sunday drinking sessions). Nowadays these old brown cafes share space with brick oven pizzerias, boutique design shops and other trappings of the young professional set. Nice to know: each of the streets is named after a flower. Close by: Westerkerk, Anne Frank Huis.
notes: Freshly made up beds and crispy towels (two per person) will be waiting for you upon arrival.
transit: The house is located right in city centre. Very close to the central station. With a bus it's less than 10 minute. You can take bus 21 or 18 and get off at Marnixplein station.

neighborhood_overview: Bos en Lommer is a diverse and family-orientated neighborhood. This district is relatively central and surrounded by parks, it is very close to the Westerpark. Bos en Lommerplein is its own Centre with a outdoor market and its surrounded with different supermarkets and clothing shops. Being chiefly residential, Bos en Lommer dwellers generally head into town for their eating, drinking and culture. However, there are many new eating and drinking opportunities along Bos en Lommerweg, with the multicultural theatre-café Podium Mozaiek, located in a former church, giving the neighborhood some social soul. The Erasmuspark is located in this district, where you can escape the busy city. It is popular to go picnicking or for a nice walk.
notes: Freshly made up beds and crispy towels (one per person) will be waiting for you upon arrival.
transit: The easiest way to get around the city is by bike, but you can also use public transport. Close to the apartment you can find different trams and buses that can take you around the whole city.

name: Traditional Canalhouse Familyhome
summary: This canalhouse was built in 1649. Initially it was built as an industrial storage for cacao and coffee beans. In the late 18th century it was re-purposed as a family home. This house has recently been restaurated to modern days standards.
space: This canal house is a warmly decorated family home. Situated in the center of Amsterdam. The view from the front side of the house is stunning. You will notice tourists taking pictures of the house all throughout the day. The house is floor 1, 2, 3 and 4.  In Amsterdam there are  restrictions that allow a max of 4 guests at a time. For groups larger than 4 I have a special offer.  We have a good relationship with our neighbors and like to keep it that way so we would like you to call yourself a friend of our family if anyone asks.

host_about:
Hi there, my name is Tara. 

I was born Dublin but have lived in Amsterdam, my whole life. I Know the way around and know where to go and not to! 
I love organizing things, can be a surprise party or just a special newspaper on the table waiting for you when you arrive.

Looking forward to your visit!
Tara

name: Spacious Amsterdam home with garden & fire place
summary: Super-comfortable authentic apartment for a lovely weekend or a week in Amsterdam. It includes all amenities to make your stay great, including 2 bikes. Explore Amsterdam and it's surroundings from this lovely neighbourhood.
space: Feel at home in our beautiful house, which we love so much. It is an apartment on the ground floor (with a recently renovated basement) in a building that is over a century old (1907). The house has been completely renovated but we kept the original details. The 'Watergraafsmeer' neighbourhood is very 'green', with lots of parks, restaurants and shops and centrally located.  The living room has a fireplace, the kitchen is equipped with everything you'll need. Annex the kitchen is a conservatory with underfloor heating, looking out onto the garden.  The modern bathroom has a lovely big rainshower. The bedroom is at the back of the house, therefore very quiet. The spacious garden is very quiet as well, especially when you consider it is in the city of Amsterdam. Needless to say it is equipped with d garden table and a barbecue.

summary: Welcome to our house. We are located in de oldest part of town, also known as the red-light district. description: This beautiful place with authentic details is absolutely perfect for exploring and discovering the magical city of Amsterdam! It’s spacious, clean and luxurious.  You will have a cosy and romantic master bedroom with a private bathroom. It’s a perfect fit for expats given the location as well as for couples (max.1 couple). The Room is available for one or two guests and contains two single beds or one kingsize double bed with fresh blankets and towels to make your stay complete. neighborhood_overview: East has its charm because of a mixture of different cultures and the new influence of young creatives. The place is located conveniently close to Amstel station and Amsterdam Central. Tram 9 next door takes you directly to Dam square within 12 minutes. There’s a possibility to rent two bikes with the apartment to explore every bit of Amsterdam. The area gives you a great feeling of old Amsterdam, There’s something for everyone. East has it all. Great restaurants, raw sheds, trendy cocktail bars, just name it! All kinds of trendy shops can be found here.
notes: The apartment is on the second floor.
transit: From Amsterdam central you can take the tram 9 (takes 15 minutes). It stops 1 minute from my place. Or you can take the train to Amsterdam Amstel station en walk 7 minutes.  The place is set in Amsterdam, within 1.9 km of Carre Theatre.  The property is situated 2.3 km from Dutch National Opera & Ballet.  The property is located in the Oost district, 2.5 km from Heineken Experience.  Museum of Bags and Purses Hendrikje is 2.5 km from the accommodation, while Rembrandtplein is 2.5 km from the property. The nearest airport is Schiphol Airport, 12 km from the property. There is a transport card specialy for toerists. Its the OV-Chipcard and you can buy this at Amsterdam Central station. It doesn’t have an expiration date so you can travel as long as you want with it.  All trams, metro's are within 2 minutes walk.  Also you can rent a bike and explore the city like all people of Amsterdam do.  Central station is 15 minutes by metro and less then 30 minutes away from the airport.
access: You’ll have access to a beautiful master bedroom with a private bathroom, a place to call your own during your stay. Please make yourself at home!
interaction: Please feel free to contact me before and during your stay. I’ll be happy to answer all your questions. I know my city very well and I would love to help you out with recommendations and getting around the city.
house_rules: - *Not safe for children (0-12 years old).  - *Flexible check in.

neighborhood_overview: Amsterdam Old South is the neighbourhood for culture and culinary delights. You don’t have to be a local in Amsterdam to know that Amsterdam Old South is one of the chicest neighbourhoods in town. The Amstelveenseweg is known for its great restaurants and check out Restaurant Bar-Grill Marathonweg. If you want to go on a shopping spree in Amsterdam Old South our top-pick streets are the Van Baerlestraat and Jacob Obrechtstraat. Smaller boutiques and a lot of specialty stores!
notes: Guests we look for: - Respectful of neighbours (keep level of noise down) - Non-smokers (or smokers that smoke outside) - Above 30 when in a group of 2 - Any age if staying as a couple At time of departure:  make sure the apartment is tidy, the dishes are done the garbage is bagged and the oven, hob and fridge/freezer are clean.  all keys must be returned upon departure. name: Fully equipped bright studio in popular old west
summary: Neat bright studio on the 4th floor, fully equipped, located in the nicest part of the popular old west district and near Vondelpark.
space: I live here myself, so it's not just a soulless apartment only used for Airbnb. There are paintings and books and I always have flowers :) It's quiet as it's located on the courtyard side and very light, because of the large windows. You can hear the birds sing.  Very practical: It's on the 4th floor, and typical Amsterdam, only accessible by stairs. The studio has a double bed, a small table with two chairs and a bench, a new kitchen with a refrigerator, washing machine, dishwasher, kettle and a microwave. You can use all the cookware and spices/herbs etc. The bathroom is small but clean and neat, a shower, sink and toilet.

neighborhood_overview: Oud-West has that great mix of cultures and economic levels which makes it a vibrant neighborhood. It’s fun to explore the posh streets near Vondelpark and the ethnic grocers on De Clercqstraat and Kinkerstraat. You’ll find lots of students and young creative people in this area, as well as families with small children. Oud-West is full of excellent restaurants, cafes and bars. If you’re craving pizza, coffee, burritos or beer you can find it all in the neighborhood.
notes: - no parties / really loud music - no smoking in the apartment, if you do: only outside te window and don't throw your butts outside, but in the ashtray instead. - do not walk/sit on the roof, it's not meant for that and dangerous.
transit: You've easy acces to public transport by tram or bus. There are stops just around the corner and lines that can bring you to the city centre or train stations to go to Schiphol airport.
interaction: During your stay I will not be there, but of course you can contact me when you've any questions. The other people living in the building are also friends of mine so they can help you out as well.
host_about:
I'm living in Amsterdam and I'm working at a creative agency as a Trendwatcher. So I know which places and events to go, I’m happy to provide you with some tips where to go that aren’t so touristy. 

I'm a cultural omnivore, I love going to the movies and visit museums and exhibitions. I'd like to have dinner with friends, go to music festivals and dance! On the other side I love my me-time to just relax, do some yoga and running. In an unfamiliar city I avoid the major tourist attractions and I rather follow the tips of the locals.

neighborhood_overview: The houseboat lies on a typical Dutch canal in a very unique street in the city center (close to central train-station). In the street you’ll find no houses, but just houseboats. This makes it a nice and quit street, while you can find busy and touristic Amsterdam just around the corner.
notes: Amsterdam has lots to offer. I’m available to make some personal recommendations if you’d like.
transit: For a real Dutch experience rent a bicycle (a 5 minute walk). You can visit most places by 30min. walk or 10minutes by bike. It sounds far, but you’ll be surprised how fast it feels going from a to b. Because there’s lots to see during the way. The other great option is taking the tram.

interaction: You can call, text or e-mail me anytime with questions in Dutch or English, I’ll be happy to answer them.

name: At the Butcher's Amsterdam Noord
summary: Do you like the city but also like some peace and quiet after a busy day? Enjoy your Amsterdam experience in our B&B! It's located NOT in the city centre but on a characteristic dike in A'dam-Noord, best of both worlds! Our house dates from the beginning of 1900.Until the end of the 60's it was the butcher of the region. In 2017 it's completely renovated. We have worked hard to realize two cosy guestrooms. From 2018 'The Butcher's Attic' can be booked. 'The Butcher's Backyard' will open mid '18.
space: The room has a private bathroom and kitchenette and is 20m2 meters (this is without the attic where you will be sleeping!). It is recently completely renovated, everything is new! Next to that: the location of the B&B is ideal: it is in a peace, quite and especially a green area but 15 minutes (push) bike from the rural centre of Amsterdam.

neighborhood_overview: Bed & Breakfast At the Butcher's is located in a beautiful, quiet and easily accessible location in Amsterdam Noord. Amsterdam Noord is unexplored and rugged, it is the greenest and largest district of Amsterdam. With the city at your fingertips! Parking is free and can be done at the door. Within fifteen minutes by bicycle and 20 minutes by bus you are at central station Amsterdam and within 5 minutes in the beautiful polder landscapes of North Holland.  Where you can go? Northern: Cycling over the monumental Waterlandse Zeedijk, towards the Zaanse Schans or to Monnickendam, Marken or Volendam. Within 10 minutes of cycling, walking, rowing or swimming in nature reserve 'het Twiske'. Good food in the IJkantine, at Loetje aan het IJ or at Pllek (5 minutes cycling). Or do you come especially for the festivals (BovenIJ Festival, ADE etc), the NDSM shipyard or for the monthly large flea market in the IJhallen? Enough to do! Southern: Take the bike and the (free) NDSM ferry (or city bus 35)
notes: We have two children (4 and 1). However we have put effort in soundproofing the rooms and our children are really sweet (:-), it may be possible that you will hear them play. We do not serve breakfast yet, we will from medio 2018.
transit: De busstop is at 500 meter (20 minutes to city centre), we rent out bicycles (15 minutes to city centre) and parking is free!
access: Own bathroom and kitchenette. You will be sleeping on a sleeping loft (see pics) Acces to the sleeping loft is via a steep staircase.
interaction: We do live in the house ourselves but the room has direct acces from the hallway so there is a lot of privacy, but if you do have questions, we are available!
host_about: My name is Merel, 38 years old, living in Amsterdam together with my boyfriend and two children (4 and 1). We've travelled a lot around the world. Last destinations were South Korea, San Fransisco to attend a wedding and West Australia to visit a childhood friend. But now... we do have to children so are fixed to schedules and holiday seasons... We live together with our cat fatty, in our beautiful renovated 'dijkhuis' which we renovated in 2017. This year we start our B&B 'at the butcher's' We wish you all very welcome!

host_about:
Hi! We are Eva & Kobe, and you're more than welcome to stay at one of the fabulous apartments and homes we manage while the home owners are on holiday. 

With our small company L'easeaway, we strive to offer you a pleasant and memorable stay in our home town: Amsterdam. We love to share the hidden gems with you, and we can provide you with all the information you need to get the most out of your stay. 

As we were awarded the 'superhost' status on airbnb, we can assure you that we will do our outmost to make your stay truly amazing. Please feel free to have a look at our +500 reviews!

Our core values are similar to the ones on which airbnb is founded, hospitality & live like a local is what's is all about. We are flexible, always available and will welcome you in person, show you around and answer all of your questions. 

Combined with the fact that our standards of cleanliness are very high, you can certainly expect our properties to be 110% clean. All our high quality bath- and bed linen are professionally steamed and ironed.  

Please feel free to contact us if you have any questions or special requests. We'll be happy to assist you! We would be delighted to host you during your stay in Amsterdam!

neighborhood_overview: The apartment is located at the picturesque Jacob van Lennepkanaal in the Oud West (‘Old West’) district.  Old West is a mix of different cultures and economic level, best characterised by its bustling everyday street market and ethnic grocers trade within a stone’s throw from 19th c. aristocratic splendour.  Go here for:  - the lively, kicking and cheap Ten Katemarkt - mostly fruit/vegetables but also some very good fish - the new Food Hallen - an old tram depot converted into a covered street food market and cinema  - Kinkerstraat and the Overtoom for a mix of specialty stores in lighting, furniture, gardening, secondhand things, unexpected things, small restaurants and ethnic cuisine.
notes: Freshly made up beds and crispy towels (one per person) will be waiting for you upon arrival. Check-in fee’s for late check-in 8PM - 12PM : 20 EUR 12PM – 2AM : 40 EUR 2AM – 9AM : 50 EUR We charge 50 EUR for nightly issues.
transit: From/To Central Station and/or City Centre you can take Tram 17 or 1 and get off at Kinkerstraat!

host_about:
Hi, I'm Martijn, 

We are a team of professional hosts established by travelers just like you. We believe in sharing homes. Wherever you are, it is delightful to explore and discover an unknown city from an authentic home. 

On behalf of home owners we advertise their properties through our airbnb profile and support them by offering you a pleasant stay. 

When you book your holiday with us, you can be confident of a memorable stay and an experience through the eyes of a local. We are more than happy to share our knowledge, give you the best insider tips and recommendations about Amsterdam.

If you have any questions, holiday wishes or simply want to have a chat, then feel free to contact us any time. We always reply within an hour!

We look forward to being your host! :)

summary: This Private Apartment overlooking a canal is located in the hip & trendy Oud-West neighbourhood! name: Great location; 2p stay!
summary: Sleeping up to 2 guests in luxury surroundings, this fantastic holiday home makes the perfect choice for your stay in Amsterdam!
space: This gorgeous apartment is excellently designed with your comfort in mind. A warm inviting living space features chic flooring throughout and deliciously contemporary furniture.  An elegant dining table and chairs enable you to make mealtimes comfortable and it’s of course the perfect time to plan tomorrow’s adventures in town together. Prepare favourite recipes from home or why not try a little Dutch cooking with local spices from the nearby convenience stores and supermarkets. neighborhood_overview: The Amsterdam Canal District is a neighborhood in Amsterdam, Netherlands. The seventeenth-century canals of Amsterdam, located in the center of Amsterdam, were added to the UNESCO World Heritage List in August 2010. The Amsterdam Canal District consists of the area around the city’s four main canals: Singel, Herengracht, Keizersgracht, and Prinsengracht. From Brouwersgracht, the canals are generally parallel with one another, leading gradually southeast into the Amstel river. Many of the canal houses in the Amsterdam Canal District are from the Dutch Golden Age in the 18th century. Many of these buildings, however, underwent restoration or reconstruction in various centuries, meaning that these building display many different architectural styles and facades.

neighborhood_overview: Amsterdam East is one of the upcoming or so called hipster neighbourhoods in Amsterdam! It almost seems that a new hotspot pops up almost every day in this neighbourhood. It’s nearby the city centre, but has such a different vibe. A drink at the rooftop of The Volkshotel is a must to enjoy the stunning views over Amsterdam! When it comes to restaurants there is something for everyone. From trendy coffee bars, industrial warehouses, cocktail bars to concept stores! The Czaar Peter Street and the Javastraat are some of the best shopping streets on the East side of town. All kinds of trendy shops can be found here. On a sunny day it’s definitely a must to visit Roest for a drink on the waterfront. If you want the local feel and multi-culti then stroll over the  Dappermarket or wander around the Oosterpark. The renewed Beukenplein is perfect for a drink afterwards!
notes: Guests we look for: - Respectful of neighbours (keep level of noise down) - Non-smokers (or smokers that smoke outside) - Guest age; above 30  At time of departure:  make sure the apartment is tidy, the dishes are done the garbage is bagged and the oven, hob and fridge/freezer are clean.  all keys must be returned upon departure. Failure to do so will incur a replacement fee.  Guests must immediately inform the host of all defects in the apartment and damages that occur in the apartment.
transit: All primary locations in the city centre are easily reached within 10/15 minutes by bike or public transport. You can rent a bike at Studio Bike, which is just at the end of the street. For the ARTIS Amsterdam Royal Zoo, Rembrandtplein and Dam square, tram 14 stops just around the corner. From Amsterdam Central Station you can take bus 22 which will take 15 minutes to the apartment. And Van Gogh museum & Rijksmuseum can be reached with tram 3 in 10 minutes. Also, Train station Muiderpoort is a 10 minute walk. This makes it very easy to get here from Schiphol airport and back.
access: You will get access to the entire apartment. Make yourself at home!
interaction: I will meet you at the apartment, handle the keys and show you around. After that feel free to contact me on Airbnb if you need any assistance or tips! I am more than happy to help you! Check in after 8PM will be an additional €15 in cash. After 10PM this will be €30.

neighborhood_overview: Our newly renovated loft is situated in the best of Amsterdam, Oud Zuid (Old South).  In just 2 minutes you are walking in the Vondelpark (The Central Park of Amsterdam) and in 10 minutes you are the museum square district by bike or tram.  When the weather is nice, the locals will relax at the Schinkelvaart canal (1 minute walk) or the Westlandgracht canal (2 minutes walk) while barbecuing, picnicking or taking the boat through the canals. The neighbourhood is also very vibrant with many shops, restaurants (including vegan), cafes and pubs open from early in the morning till late at night. Also many supermarkets are around for your daily groceries. Public transportation such as bus (5 meters away), tram (20 meters away) which will take you directly from and to Central station and metro (2 stops away) are in a walking distance.  Highway: Easy access to the highway A10
notes: Check-in & Check-out The check-in time is 14:00 and the check out is 11:00 a.m.  Public transportation: Direct bus line to airport. Tram 2 (just 1 min walk) will take you to the center.  Quick access to the highway. Parking Parking places are available in the street; however it’s paid parking till midnight except for Sunday.
transit: How to get to our loft: By plane & public transportation When you arrive at Schiphol Airport: 1) Train (NS) and bus (GVB) Take from the airport the train to Amsterdam Zuid station. Then take the bus line 15 in the direction of Sloterdijk from the train station Amsterdam Zuid. Get off at bus stop Hoofddorpplein and you are in front of the building. By car: When driving to Amsterdam take the A10 South highway and take exit s107. In our street you can park your car. Mind you it is paid parking till midnight.
access: The access will be via the main entrance of the building. There you will find the staircase which will take you directly to the 4th floor where the loft is.
interaction: Upon your arrival, we will welcome you and give you a quick tour and explain you how everything works. We will also tell you a bit more about the area, as we are locals, and answer any possible questions you may have,  After this, we will give you the keys to the building main entrance and to the loft.

neighborhood_overview: De Pijp (""The Pipe""), formerly a working class neigbourhood is now definitely one of the most popular areas of Amsterdam. Within walking distance from the city centre (and the RAI Convention Centre)  - but just outside of the stressfully busy areas - this ""typical Amsterdam"" neighbourhood offers a fantastic selection of shops, cafes, bars and restaurants and is often referred to as Amsterdam's ""Latin Quarter"" and one of the ""coolest"" and ""bohemian"" parts of the city. This apartment is 8 minutes' walk from the famous Albert Cuyp Street Market, 5 minutes from the Sarphatipark and 13 minutes' walk from the Heineken Experience.  Also nearby is the Museumplein where you can visit the Van Gogh Museum, Stedelijk Museum, National Concert Hall (Concertgebouw),  and the famous recently re-opened Rijksmuseum where you can take fun photos of yourself with the IAMSTERDAM letters.  Amsterdam RAI convention center is a short 15 minute walk to the south, and the Jordaan and Oud West (Old West) neighbo

summary: A unique accommodation in a serene environment combining the best of both worlds. Enjoy this tranquil setting on a luxurious houseboat providing you with the privacy you may need at only ten minutes from the center of Amsterdam, easy to reach by bus, bike ferry or Uber. Besides free and secure parking, use the classic Dutch bikes to cycle along one of Amsterdam's most authentic areas with turn of the century houses and pubs.
space: Entrance via the rear deck decorated with pots & plants and a wooden dinner table, leading into the charming full-service kitchen with dining area that seats up to 6 people. Downstairs: Large living room with fantastic light from large roof windows. Watch the blue skies or stars at night from your hanging hammock chair or enjoy a movie on the large flat screen TV with cannot get much more adventurous at a stone's throw away from the vibrant city center of Amsterdam. Jump off the boat into the water for a refreshing swim. At the very front of the boat you reach the bedroom and a bathroom with shower. There is one master bedroom with a double bed and luxury mattress for a superb night sleep (Goossens award winning Infinity mattress ). Extra bed can be arranged by a Kingsize inflatable mattress.

neighborhood_overview: Arrive at the marina, located in one of Amsterdam’s most authentic neighbourhoods, lined with round of the century wooden houses, cafes and bars. The famous cafe bar 'het sluisje' is only a few feet away. This is real dutch living, with few cars, and cafes and bars serving local cuisine and a variety of dutch and belgian beers only a short stroll away. A perfect place for fishing, kayaking, paddling, nature walks, tennis, jogging and swimming. Venture further with bus or bike for more restaurants and entertainment. A truly beautiful spot whether you want a quiet retreat, or enjoy it to the fullest with your family.
transit: Free parking on secure marina car park free of charge. The bus stop is only a few minutes walk and a ten minute ride will take you straight into town. Use our classic dutch rental bikes to either cycle to town over the big bridge, or to the ferry, which will take you across to the centre of town within minutes and free of charge. Alternatively, a taxi or Uber will take you to town for around €15.

name: Bed&Breakfast @ Miami Vice
summary: We used to travel with our yacht overseas, but not anymore. It's permanent moored to our houseboat in the north part of Amsterdam and you are welcome to stay. A very special way to experience your Amsterdam stay.
space: To get to the yacht you will pass our garden on the left side with a steep path down. There are a few steps up to the wooden walkway around our houseboat. From the roofed terrace on the back deck of the boat you enter the wheelhouse/sitting area.  A big comfy sofa offers you a relaxed place to sit.  A few steps down you'll find the master bedroom with bathroom ensuite.  On the other side of the yacht you'll find the kitchen area. The kitchen is fully equipped with everything you might need during your stay. With an electric stove, microwave, fridge, freezer, coffee maker and kettle. And another table to sit with 4 people for a nice breakfast, lunch or dinner.  The next room is the second bedroom with 2 single beds, right next to this bedroom you'll find the second bathroom. We have bikes on the premises which you can rent.  - cable TV + Wi-Fi are free of charge - towels & bed linen are provided - no smoking inside the boat (feel free to smoke on the deck) - no noise and parties

summary: Sleeping up to 2 guests in luxury surroundings, this fantastic holiday home makes the perfect choice for your stay in Amsterdam!
space: This gorgeous apartment is excellently designed with your comfort in mind. A warm inviting living space features chic wooden flooring throughout and deliciously contemporary furniture. neighborhood_overview: Amsterdam East is one of the upcoming or so called hipster neighbourhoods in Amsterdam! It almost seems that a new hotspot pops up almost every day in this neighbourhood. It’s nearby the city centre, but has such a different vibe. A drink at the rooftop of The Volkshotel is a must to enjoy the stunning views over Amsterdam! When it comes to restaurants there is something for everyone. From trendy coffee bars, industrial warehouses, cocktail bars to concept stores! The Czaar Peter Street and the Javastraat are some of the best shopping streets on the East side of town. All kinds of trendy shops can be found here. On a sunny day it’s definitely a must to visit Roest for a drink on the waterfront. If you want the local feel and multi-culti then stroll over the  Dappermarket or wander around the Oosterpark. The renewed Beukenplein is perfect for a drink afterwards!
notes: Guests we look for: - Respectful of neighbours (keep level of noise down) - Non-smokers (or smokers that smoke outside) - Above 30 when in a group of 4 - Any age if staying as a responsible couple At time of departure:  Leave the home as tidy as you found it. make sure the apartment is tidy, the dishes are done the garbage is bagged and the oven, hob and fridge/freezer are clean.  all keys must be returned upon departure. Failure to do so will incur a replacement fee. You can leave them on the table. Guests must immediately inform the host of all defects in the apartment and damages that occur in the apartment.
access: You will get access to the entire apartment. Make yourself at home!
interaction: I will meet you at a location near the Central Station, handle the keys and apartment info. After that feel free to contact me on Airbnb if you need any assistance or tips! I am more than happy to help you! Check in after 8 pm will be an additional €15 in cash. After 10 pm will be €30 in cash.

host_about:
Hi! We are Eva & Kobe, and you're more than welcome to stay at one of the fabulous apartments and homes we manage while the home owners are on holiday. 

With our small company L'easeaway, we strive to offer you a pleasant and memorable stay in our home town: Amsterdam. We love to share the hidden gems with you, and we can provide you with all the information you need to get the most out of your stay. 

As we were awarded the 'superhost' status on airbnb, we can assure you that we will do our outmost to make your stay truly amazing. Please feel free to have a look at our +500 reviews!

Our core values are similar to the ones on which airbnb is founded, hospitality & live like a local is what's is all about. We are flexible, always available and will welcome you in person, show you around and answer all of your questions.

name: Private room in colourful, cozy house in top area
summary: Welcome to our cozy house. My brother, I and our cat live in a perfectly located ground floor apartment. The house is decorated with warm colours, filled with books and there is lots to see on the walls.  Anybody who is kind, clean and considerate is welcome in our home. It is an easy journey from airport to our house. The fastest route is taking a train to Station Rai. From there, jump on tram number 4 and jump off at the stop 'Lutmastraat'. A few minutes walk and you are there.
space: Bedroom  The bedroom we offer you has a queen size bed with two pillows and one blanket. Extra blanket is available upon request. There is space to hang your clothes. There are two lights, a main light and a little bed light. There is an electricity supply for chargers and i provide with ear plugs (see below). The bedroom has a window., which can be opened and closed. It is a sky window, so you would have to use the couch as a step-on to reach the handle. There is a heater, which is easy to control.  Bathroom We share one bathroom, including the toilet, which is kept clean and tidy. Extra clean towels are always available. There is a shower space and  a spacious sink for two persons. Shampoo and shower gel are available.  Living There is an open living space with kitchen, kitchen table, seating area and television. The table has two chairs. The couch can seat two to three people and there is an extra chair. With warm weather we open the doors to the street and enjoy the access to outdo

neighborhood_overview: The area is called 'the Pijp' and considered one of the most popular areas in Amsterdam. The beautiful Sarphatipark and famous Albert Cuyp Market are around the corner.  The Heineken Experience is walking distance and so is the Museum Square, where you can visit impressive museums, such as Vincent van Gogh Museum and the Rijksmuseum. That same area holds the elegant Vondelpark, a must see when visiting Amsterdam. Downtown Amsterdam is easy to reach by tram, metro, or even better, by bicycle. The Rembrandt Square is very nearby.  At the end of the street, you can cross the river Amstel and find yourself in 'East', a vibrant area filled with amazing spots.
notes: We have a friendly cat, who sleeps on the couch in the living room or plays outside in the neighbourhood. Please don't bring other people back home with you, and no loud noises after 10 pm - we and the neighbours like sleeping early during the week.  Shoes off in the house is much appreciated. Smoking is not allowed.
transit: By tram 4 you reach downtown. If you take tram 4 the other way, you reach Station Rai from where a train takes you to the airport within 10 minutes. Tram 3 takes you to the beautiful East area of Amsterdam, or the other way to the Museum Square and the Vondelpark. The metro is on a walking distance and takes you to any part of Amsterdam. The quickest, easiest and most sustainable way to get around is a bicycle, which you can rent from several places nearby the house.
access: We share with you the open living area, kitchen and bathroom.  You will receive your own key and you can come and go as you please. This is a residential property, so please have respect for the space, privacy and good night's rest of the neighbours. Keep in mind that we are quiet between 10pm and 8am.
interaction: My brother and I both work, but during the evening we love to stay in, cook and watch television. If we are home at the same time as you are, we are up for having a coffee or wine together and tell you where the best spots in the city are :)
house_rules: We lock the front door on a double lock, 24/7. Quiet hours after 11 PM. We take our shoes off at the door to keep the house clean.
host_about: Amsterdam is my home town. I have lived abroad many years. I love talking to people from all backgrounds and exchanging views and experiences. I am very well-organized, clean and tidy. I find comfort in simplicity.

Once at the Spui, walk into the Spui Square, just a few steps walk in the direction the tram is proceeding. You will see a bar called ""Hoppe"" (established 340 years ago) and a small alleyway on it's right called the Heisteeg. Walk to the end of the alleyway and then cross the canals in front of you. You will walk over 3 bridges until you get onto the Runstraat, 5 minutes walk from the Spuistraat tram stop. Should you require assistance in finding us just ask someone for directions to the Runstraat or ""Gerda's flower store"" and the ""Doffer"" cafe, two well-known local attractions across the road from us.
