host_about:
Hi, I'm Vero (Veronique)

37,  Dutch/American, grew up in South East Asia, and wound up settling down in Amsterdam for the past 11 years after College in Maine. 1 year became 11 the way life goes :) Speaks highly for Amsterdam's appeal. I fell in love with it's down-to-earth, healthy, village-like city feel. 

I'm an Ayurvedic Life style practitioner, holistic masseuse, healthy meals cook, and English language consultant. 
Also addicted to my daily dose of hot/hatha yoga. Happy to give guests tips of  what Amsterdam has to offer relating to Holistic activities, dining etc.

The first 6 years of my time in Amsterdam I owned an art gallery specialising in Contemporary Chinese and Vietnamese painting. Amsterdam has much to offer on the art front for those into the art scene.

For guests who are interested, there is the option of having massage treatments or Ayurvedic consultations should you stay with me. Those wanting more information can inquire at check-in.

I love meeting guests from all over the world and having them stay.
I have a ragdoll cat who thinks he's a dog and loves people. He stays on my wing of the flat unless guests want to give the little tiger a cuddle.

I love wine and good food, nature walks, everything from ballet to opera and soul, warm travel destinations or city-trips and being creative in general.

Looking forward to meeting those of you who stay with me!

Namaste,
Vero

name: Clean & cosy studio in canal rings (own entrance)
summary: A recently renovated and beautifully styled private bedroom - complete with an own private entrance and private bathroom. Located in the heart of the city and a stones throw away from all the famous museums (Rykes, Van Gogh, Banksy), key sights (Canals, Prinsengracht), galleries (Spiegelkwartier), shops and restaurants (Leidseplein). The apartment is a typical Amsterdam apartment and the street is charming and characteristic of Amsterdam, and so if you’re in for an authentic experience, then this is the perfect accommodation for you.
space: I love our studio room. It's has a really stylish, nice, and cosy vibe. Being on the 3nd floor the studio has an attic window and skylight over the bathroom with means that it is filled with beautiful natural daylight - which is quite unique for Amsterdam ;). It's set up for guests as a living room during the daytime and when you want to sleep all you need to do is pull on the shelf and the couch converts itself easily into bed (it’s a space saving wall bed unit) which gives the studio lots of versatility in terms of maximizing living and sleeping areas. It’s a great place to reside and feel at home after an exiting day exploring around this beautiful city.

neighborhood_overview: It’s hard to find a better neighborhood than this. So much to see and do! Although in the heart of action and things to do, the street is quiet, full of other houses with quintessential Dutch character and feels residential - perfect if you want an authentic experience. It's located right near the grand and palatial Rijksmuseum, a short walk from the famous Heiniken Experience museum and 2 streets either side from the picturesque Amsterdam canals. Around the corner you'll find a plethora of galleries, shops, theaters/cinemas and dining and evening entertainment possibilities. The apartment is a 8min walk to the buzzing Leidesplein, 10 mins walk from the Amstel, 15 mins walk to the renown ""9 streets"" in the historic Jordaan area. Also a short walk to “de Pijp” - Amsterdam’s hip area for locals with great shops, restaurants, and bars, not the mention the famous “Albert Cuyp Market”. Last but not least it’s a short 5min walk to the P.C Hooftstraat (Pieter Cornelisz Hooftstraat), Amsterdam
notes: Our beautiful studio is nestled in a typical Dutch style building, meaning two key things:  1) You may find the hallway stairwell steep. So those with a lot of heavy luggage please note that you’ll have an authentic “Dutch experience” getting up and down the stairs ;) 2) It’s a quiet residential building and the walls are thin, so we ask all guest if they could please respect the neighbors when coming in and out of the building by not slamming the door or walking loudly up and down the stairs.
transit: Getting to the apartment:  We have an excellent choice of bus and tram connections from Weteringschans & Leideseplein.  The 397 bus will take you straight from the airport (catch it from bus stop B15 and costs just 5eur) to the Rijksmuseum, from where the apartment is a short 5min walk. From central station there are several tram connections which will stop within 300m of the apartment. A taxi from central will take you ca. 4mins to get here, depending on traffic. Getting around AMSTERDAM: We highly recommend you adopt the full Dutch mentality while here and hire a bike. It’s the most cost and time efficient way to get around. 300m down the street there is a great bike rental place called “Het Zwarte Fietsenplan” in the Lijnbaansgracht where you can rent bikes. The city is not so big, and this way you can cover a lot in less time.  Alternatively Uber is a handy!
access: Access to the apartment is via the outer stairwell and it's the first door (the left door) facing the stairs. The studio apartment is on the 3nd floor with it’s own private access. Meaning it functions similar to a hotel room. In the studio you have a living room/bedroom with a bench style table, a wardrobe to hang clothing, shelf space, built in kitchenette (sink, stove, oven, fridge) including tea & coffee, plus an ensuite bathroom (with toilet, sink & shower).  Please note, as we have separate doors, no access to our main apartment is granted, but feel free to knock on our door in case you need something or for any questions. If we are around, we would be more than happy to help you :)
interaction: Pre/during/post stay: In case you have any questions or comments, please don't hesitate to contact me directly to ask and I’ll do my best to help you out!  Please note, as we have separate doors, no access to our main apartment is granted, but feel free to knock on our door in case you need something or for any questions. If we are around, we would be more than happy to help you :)
house_rules: It’s important that guest recognize that they are in a residential home/building. No parties or loud guest. As it’s an old Amsterdam building it’s important to respect our neighbors and to be quiet in the hallway particularly when opening/closing doors and going up/down the stairs.

space: Als gast huur je de gehele benedenwoning met tuin. De woning heeft een ruime woonkamer met zithoek, eethoek en keuken.  Je komt binnen in een hal, met deur naar de nieuwe badkamer en toilet en naar de woonkamer. Vanuit de ruime woonkamer met open keuken loop je naar kamer 1 (slaapkamer) en kamer 2 (extra kamer). In kamer 2 kan een luxe luchtbed worden geplaatst. Vanuit kamer 2 loop je zo de grote vernieuwde tuin in. Foto’s van de nieuwe tuin volgen nog.

name: Apt. with garden!
summary: Sleeping up to 2 guests in luxury surroundings, this fantastic holiday home makes the perfect choice for your stay in Amsterdam!
space: This gorgeous apartment is excellently designed with your comfort in mind. A warm inviting living space features chic wooden flooring throughout and deliciously contemporary furniture.  An elegant dining table and chairs enable you to make mealtimes comfortable and it’s of course the perfect time to plan tomorrow’s adventures in town together. Prepare favourite recipes from home or why not try a little Dutch cooking with local spices from the nearby convenience stores and supermarkets. The fantastic fitted kitchen is packed with all the equipment you need to create something delicious. The pretty bedroom is stylishly presented and features unfussy earth tones to encourage restful sleep and there is ample storage for your belongings.  The apartment also features a private bathroom fitted with a sink, shower, bath and toilet. Enjoy the outdoor space!

neighborhood_overview: Amsterdam Old South is the neighbourhood for culture and culinary delights. You don’t have to be a local in Amsterdam to know that Amsterdam Old South is one of the chicest neighbourhoods in town. The Amstelveenseweg is known for its great restaurants and check out Restaurant Bar-Grill Marathonweg. If you want to go on a shopping spree in Amsterdam Old South our top-pick streets are the Van Baerlestraat and Jacob Obrechtstraat. Smaller boutiques and a lot of specialty stores!

name: Amy & Paul’s Home from home
summary: We offer our entire home in a quieter area of Amsterdam which is still very close to the Center, it’s a 20 min walk to the Jordaan or 10 mins by bike. Also public transport options close by. We have 2 bedrooms and a cozy lounge, dining area and big garden with garden sofa to chill on. The house is newly refurbished and a very cosy place to stay.  We also have a young cat called Ralph who will also welcome you on your stay.
space: We have 2 bedrooms, one main bedroom with a big double bed and the second with a very cosy and comfortable day bed which told out into a comfortable double.  The bathroom is clean and modern with a rain shower.  The kitchen is small but perfectly formed with all utensils that you need.  The lounge and dinning room is modern with a vintage twist. The space is open and perfect for having a lounge on the sofa.  The garden is spacious and green with a comfy big garden sofa and hammock. It’s the perfect place to chill in the morning in the sun.  The whole apartment has recently been refurbished.

name: Comfortable and cosy studio with private bathroom
summary: Comfortable and cosy studio with private bathroom and FREE parking located in the best area of Amsterdam. Safe and quiet, only 20 minutes from the City center and nature and the beach at walking distance.
space: Enjoy your weekend in Amsterdam by staying in the best area to visit Amsterdam. Safe and quiet and only 20 minutes from the City center. The  studio is located in the urban, residential area called IJburg and nature and Amsterdam’s most famous beach are only at walking distance. Start your day with a cup of coffee or tea, go for a walk or run in Diemer Park, take a shower in your private bathroom, have breakfast at Bagels & Beans or one of the many spots in the City center. Explore Amsterdam’s unique  city center with many museums, restaurants and bars and return to your comfortable bed for a quiet night to get energized for the next day! In summer you can enjoy the afternoon at our beach and have a drink and dinner at ‘Blijburg at the Sea’.  The studio is furnished with a 2-person bed, a large wardrobe, a foldable wall-mounted table with two foldable chairs. The studio has all the equipment neccesary to make your stay even more comfortable. It is equiped with a Nespresso coffee machin

neighborhood_overview: Our studio is located in the modern neighbourhood IJburg in Amsterdam East and is easily accessible both by car and public transport. We can offer you one free parking space, and you can get to the centre of Amsterdam by tram in just 15 minutes. We also offer rental bikes for only EUR 15,- per bike for your  whole stay. The neighbourhood IJburg was built on a number of artificial islands in the IJmeer. The combination of water, air, and urban atmosphere makes IJburg a unique location. Here, you are ‘outside the city’ but can get to the city centre of Amsterdam by tram within 20 minutes. IJburg has a lot to offer in terms of architecture. There are urban villas and a water district with floating homes, dike houses, and jetties. The shopping centre of IJburg is situated on your way to the City center. A small, cosy harbour with a number of restaurants is just a 5-minute walk away. Also at walking distance is the beach of IJburg with the beach pavilion Blijburg which is open throughout th
notes: Make yourself at home!
transit: Tram, bus, taxi or bicycle. Tram 26 takes you directly to Amsterdam Central station/City Center.  More info on public transportation can be found on gvb.nl We also rent out bikes. EUR 15,- per bike for the whole stay. No deposit.
access: Hallway and studio
interaction: After we’ve welcomed you to our place, Björn and I will always be at your disposal through text or phone. We both have our regular work, but when we are home we’ll certainly have time for a chat!

neighborhood_overview: Few places in Amsterdam have undergone the transformation that de Pijp has in the last 20 years. Once considered a claustrophobic workers neighbourhood with small leaky houses, it’s now home to a multitude of creatives, young families and start ups and is absolutely exploding with the internationally oriented bars and restaurants to cater to them all with the Albert Cuyp (a seemingly never-ending street market) as the beating heart of it all. The area is intersected by the Ceintuurbaan, leaving its northern half with the charming Sarphatipark, and the southern part with its special Japanese shops and restaurants, crowned by the presence of the Okura hotel and its multiple (Japanese) Michelin starred restaurants.  Close to: Amsterdam Oost, Zuid, RIJKS, Van Gogh Museum, Stedelijk Museum, MoCo Museum.
notes: Freshly made up beds and crispy towels (one per person) will be waiting for you upon arrival.
transit: In just 15 minutes you will be in the city centre! Just take the Tram: tramlines 24 and 4 will bring you there!

host_about:
Hi, I'm Martijn, 

We are a team of professional hosts established by travelers just like you. We believe in sharing homes. Wherever you are, it is delightful to explore and discover an unknown city from an authentic home. 

On behalf of home owners we advertise their properties through our airbnb profile and support them by offering you a pleasant stay. 

When you book your holiday with us, you can be confident of a memorable stay and an experience through the eyes of a local. We are more than happy to share our knowledge, give you the best insider tips and recommendations about Amsterdam.

If you have any questions, holiday wishes or simply want to have a chat, then feel free to contact us any time. We always reply within an hour!

We look forward to being your host! :)

host_about: I am a 31 year old  born and raised Amsterdammer and freelance cultural programmer. I love to ride my bicycle through the city, wander around in the parks or stroll down the Dappermarkt in the East-Side of the city. For me Amsterdam is a city with a thriving and addictive uplifting energy, bursting of cultural events. The way it looks and smells during springtime is almost poetic and makes me fall in love with it every time. I love hosting people from all over the world to show them my city.

summary: My apartment is a lovely, light and cosy place, yet spacious. It is in a quiet area but very near to the city centre. There is a balcony at the back of the house where you can enjoy the afternoon sun. The area is safe to walk around at night, and neighbors are quiet so a good sleep is guaranteed. I am happy to give you many tips!

neighborhood_overview: My neighbourhood is very close to two nice parks.  The Rembrandtpark is litterally around the corner and is very green and usually not too crowded. Many kinds of birds can be spotted in this park. There are two nice coffee bars along the park: Bartack and De Huiskamer van Rembrandt (I also list them under 'Bars and restaurants', see below). I prefer the last one as it is cosy and has great home made dishes. The owner Judith is also very nice. At a five minute walking distance from my house you find the famous Vondelpark. Worth visiting, though far more crowded than the Rembrandtpark. Supermarket:  The nearest supermarket is only one minute away and is called Albert Heijn (AH), located on the Postjesweg right behind the Postjeskade. Bars and restaurants: There are several very nice coffee bars and restaurants in my neighbourhood. Some suggestions: Bartack, Postjesweg 124 (next to Rembrandtpark)  Huiskamer van Rembrandt, Orteliuskade 5 Edel, Postjesweg 1 Café Kostverloren, Tweede Kostver
notes: Please keep in mind that the walls are thin and noise is heard easily. If you enter the building late at night, please stay quiet. Please lock my apartment's front door and the balcony door at all times and close windows when you leave the apartment, and never leave the key inside the door when leaving the house. Smoking is not allowed in my apartment, only on the balcony (use the ashtray please). All drugs are forbidden to take into house or to use, no weed smoking on balcony either. Thank you.
transit: How to get to Postjeskade 45-1 from Schiphol Airport and from train station Amsterdam Centraal: From Schiphol Airport take the train to Amsterdam Lelylaan, this ride is only 7 minutes. Then take tram 17 destination Amsterdam Centraal, get out at tram stop called Postjesweg/Hoofdweg. From trainstation Amsterdam Centraal take tram 17 destination Osdorp  Dijkgraafplein, get out at tram stop called Postjesweg/Hoofdweg. Tram stop Postjesweg/Hoofdweg is on a bridge at the crossroads. Postjeskade is the street along the water, parallel to the Postjesweg. How to get to the city centre by tram: take tram 17, destination Centraal Station, this tram takes you right through the city centre. Taxi: there are regular taxi's in Jan Pieter Heijestraat, a trip to the centre will cost you around 15 Euros. Amsterdam also houses many Uber taxis, they are a bit less expensive. You can find everything you need here at walking distance or even right in the street: lots of bars, restaurants, supermarkets and the famous Anne Franks house & the ‘Noordermarkt’, where they serve the best apple pie in town. Don’t forget to wander around all the little streets, you’ll defenitely want to get lost here.

name: Houseboat Amsterdam centre on nieuwe prinsengracht
summary: Welcome to the our houseboat! This 80 m2 houseboat in the centre of Amsterdam is perfect to experience this fabulous city in a beautiful part of town in a unique way. The houseboat is situated in a quiet residential area (De Plantage) in the city centre near Artis Zoo and the UvA. The rest of the centre is easily reachable by foot. Transport links to every major attraction in the city are very nearby. Renting this houseboat enables you to live like a real Amsterdammer. Welcome on board!
space: To wake up in the morning with the reflection of the sunlight on the surface of the water and hear the water birds singing is a unique way to live within the city. We would like to share this experience of living on a houseboat in a remote, green part of the city but still in the centre on the canals of Amsterdam. We, Bob, Esther and our son of five years old Otis, live on this comfortable houseboat, without any neighbours on the opposite side. We’d love to welcome you in our house! The houseboat is very light, spacious and modern with big windows in the living room and an open, fully equipped kitchen. The bathroom has everything you need; toilet, shower, washing machine and dryer.  The bedroom has a comfortable king-size bed (1.80 x 2.10). Outside there are two terraces were you can enjoy your breakfast or a coffee or wine in the afternoon/ evening.

neighborhood_overview: The houseboat is located in the center of Amsterdam, on the Nieuwe Prinsengracht. It's only a three minute walk from the metro and the trams.  The houseboat  is situated in a very green area of the city center, near Waterlooplein, Amstel river and Artis.   Shops, bars, restaurants, (super)markets, the zoo, parks and museums are all within walking distance.
notes: The first necessities will be ready for you: coffee and tea, toilet paper and shampoo are provided.  Several supermarkets are located within 100 meters and on the corner of the street is a Bagel&Beans which serves breakfast from 7:00 o'clock on. We're looking forward to welcoming you in our home and offer you a great stay in Amsterdam! This is our private home, so please treat it as you would treat your own.
transit: Public transport is available within 100 meters from the houseboat. Schiphol Airport takes 20 minutes by taxi and 45 minutes by train and subway.
access: The complete houseboat (80 m2) will be rented out. There is one bedroom available for our guests,one bathroom and a spacious living room, with fully equipped kitchen. Also the two terraces are available for our guests.
interaction: The bed will be made and the first necessities will be ready for you. I like to tell you about things to do in the city, so don't hesitate to ask your questions.

name: Stylish authentic entire apartment in Amsterdam!
summary: Cozy & modern apartment right next to Oosterpark and very close to cool bars, restaurants and local amenities!
description: Cozy & modern apartment right next to Oosterpark and very close to cool bars, restaurants and local amenities! Our apartment is few steps away from the Oosterpark! Within short walking distance, you have access to all necessary amenities (supermarkets, bio supermarkets, bakery, pharmacy and even hospital) There are plenty options for bars, coffee places and restaurants. Our street is quiet and residential. It is the easiest to get around from our place by bike, tram and metro. Trams 9, 3 & 7 will take you to the city center and closeby neighborhoods. Metro (5min walk) takes you to Amsterdam Central train station within 10min. The train station is also accesible (15min walk) and connects you to main connexion points. You can also use your car from here to any location. We recommend to try renting a bike for the real amsterdam experience! Rental places are located closeby.

neighborhood_overview: Have you ever had the feeling that all of the world’s shopping streets pretty much have the same stuff on offer? Well then, you need to visit Amsterdam’s Haarlemmerstraat – it’s hip, it’s quirky and it’s the perfect spot for hours of relaxed browsing, dining and bar-hopping! Independent entertainment Located in Amsterdam’s Jordaan district, the Haarlemmerstraat – and its extension, the Haarlemmerdijk - is a gem. Offering independent boutiques and speciality stores, little salons, trendy but affordable restaurants and bars and the oldest cinema in Amsterdam, this area will appeal to even the most jaded of world travellers. You are guaranteed to find a special little something from Amsterdam in this alternative shopping district. And with a constant passing parade along the Haarlemmerstraat, you can spend a very entertaining time just watching the world go by. Wide variety With 235 stores offering fashion and accessories, toys, gifts, jewellery, books, electronics and specialty delicates
transit: The house is a 10 minutes walk from the central station. We always take the train to the airfield and back. If you come by car, you can unload your stuff. You don't need a car.You can walk, take trams or use our bicycles, as we do. We can advise you were to leave your car in the meantime. When you come by car, it is the best to first unload your car in de Vinkenstraat, then take it to a Park &Ride. The nearest Park en Ride is Sloterdijk.  address: Piarcoplein 1 1043 DW  Amsterdam hi-way A10, exit S102  You park your car and then take the train to Central station.  The costs are EUR 8 per day. Railway tickets are included. Make shore you get the parking tickets before you park in order to get this price.
access: Fist of all, you don't need to bring anything, everything is arranged for. So sheets and towels are available. Sometimes we will be on holiday at the moment that you are coming. But there will always be someone to give you the keys.

neighborhood_overview: The Canal house is located in the centre on the east side of Amsterdam in the green and tranquil Plantage district – otherwise known as the “cultural garden” of the city. This quiet residential area is easy to access and in the heart of the city, however offers a peaceful and relaxing place to call home surrounded by nature and greenery.  It’s just a 15 minute walk from Central Station but a whole world away from the hustle and bustle of the vibrant city centre. No wonder the Plantage (or East Canal) district is considered by locals and visitors alike to be one of the best neighborhoods in this amazing city right now. Hop on a bike or head out for a casual stroll and you’ll find museums, parks,  bars and restaurants along the many canals that crisscross the area.
notes: Public Transport is close by, you will love our house!  If you have questions let us know!
transit: Our house is in a great spot for getting practically anywhere in the city - but you'll be surprised by how peaceful and quiet the area is. The closest tram stops are at Artis, Plantage Lepellaan and Weesperplein (numbers 9, 10 and 14). The nearest metro stations are Waterlooplein and Weesperplein. Cycling is probably the best way to get around and fit in with the locals – although not for the faint-hearted - and it’s very easy to rent bikes in Amsterdam. You can easily walk to Amsterdam Central Station but if you prefer, take metro lines 51, 53 or 54 from Waterlooplein or tram line 9 from Artis. To get to and from Schiphol airport, take metro line 51 from Weesperplein to Amsterdam Zuid station then take a train from the same station on to the airport (they’re very frequent). You could also go via Amsterdam Central Station.
access: Two floors are available for our guests and you have your own entrance.
interaction: When you book our house we will not be there only to give you the keys. Please keep in mind our neighbors and upstairs neighbors can be at home.

neighborhood_overview: The Amsterdam Canal District is a neighborhood in Amsterdam, Netherlands. The seventeenth-century canals of Amsterdam, located in the center of Amsterdam, were added to the UNESCO World Heritage List in August 2010. The Amsterdam Canal District consists of the area around the city’s four main canals: Singel, Herengracht, Keizersgracht, and Prinsengracht. From Brouwersgracht, the canals are generally parallel with one another, leading gradually southeast into the Amstel river. Many of the canal houses in the Amsterdam Canal District are from the Dutch Golden Age in the 18th century. Many of these buildings, however, underwent restoration or reconstruction in various centuries, meaning that these building display many different architectural styles and facades.

Nearby Maasstraat has many shops and bars. If you want to downtown you can do that easily in 25 minutes walking - the way is through trendy neighborhoods with restaurants and bars all along the way.
notes: Some repairs of the apartment are still outstanding: missing carpet on the entrance stairs and a wall that shows the bricks. Nothing that would impact your stay but good to know to come with the right expectations that it is not perfect.
transit: Connected with Tram 4 and 12 you can either go directly to Rembrandplein and downtown/Centraal (4) or to Museumsplein and the Van Gogh or Rijksmuseum. Bikes can be rented for an additional charge during your stay. If you need a car you can take a car2go (with designated parking areas right outside of the apartment).
access: This is an apartment in a building with two other private apartments (owners live there full time). It is important to be quiet in the hallway up to the apartment as well as to keep to the quiet hours.
interaction: Host/owner on site.

name: Pretty studio on a ship in the Heart of Amsterdam
summary: The Morgenster is a iron ship, build in 1905. In de front end we've created a lovely studio with an high end bathroom. It's just a ten minute walk from the Central Station. It's very light, due to the large windows in the ceiling. The neighbourhood od the ship is very spacious, given the fact that's in the heart of the centre of Amsterdam.
space: The studio comes with free wifi and a smart tv with Netflix on it.
description: The Morgenster is a iron ship, build in 1905. In de front end we've created a lovely studio with an high end bathroom. It's just a ten minute walk from the Central Station. It's very light, due to the large windows in the ceiling. The neighbourhood od the ship is very spacious, given the fact that's in the heart of the centre of Amsterdam. The studio comes with free wifi and a smart tv with Netflix on it. When entering the ship at the bottom of a small stairs there is a door to the left. That door is the entrance to the studio. The door to the right is the entrance to the rest of the ship where we live. The ship is located at a ten minutes walk from the Dam square, The Waterlooplein square, the Portugese synagoge, the red light district, the maritime museum, the Rembrandthouse, the Muziekgebouw aan het IJ and the NEMO science museum. The Anne Frank house is a 25 minutes walk away, as is the Rembrandt square.
notes: My neighbours cross the Morgenster on the way to their ships. You will hear them passing over. That's part of living on a ship like this.

name: LEIDSEPLEIN PRESIDENTIAL SUITE WITH A LOVELY VIEW
summary: Right at your doorstep is the famous Leidseplein Square, vibrating with bars, restaurants, clubs and theatres. Surrounding the square there are many terraces where you can sit and chill out, sip a drink while people watching or just be entertained by street bands or performers.
space: Tasteful and comfortable, this 2-bedroom serviced apartment is all set for your business trip to Amsterdam. Located in a beautifully restored building dating back to the 1900's, the lush and lavish decor will make you think twice about heading home at the end of your stay. Inside, the shades of grey easily complement the wooden floors and natural light that streams in from large bay windows throughout the day. The main bedroom is beautifully decorated with a canopy bed and, like the second bedroom, is draped in luscious linen that will have you unwinding into a natural sleep in no time at all. The second bedroom is furnished with twin beds and is comfortable and serene. For extra sleeping space, there is a sofa bed that can accommodate two additional guests. The dining area and fully functional kitchen offer a great space to flex your inner chef and to host guests, both professional and personal. The bathroom is chic and includes both shower and bath, perfect for a long nights’ soak. Y

summary: Shared open space in a lovely two-storey apartment on the peaceful and modern IJburg, Amsterdam. The air-mattress bed is located in our open living room as shown in the pictures. Me and my husband also live in the apartment in a separate bedroom.  15 minutes by tram 26 to Central station. The apartment is next to a beautiful lake where you can go jogging in the morning.
space: There is a spacious, light kitchen on the ground floor with a storage room behind, in which some luggage can be stored. Upstairs is a large living room which also doubles as the guest room, as seen on the photos. Further there is a bathroom and separate lavatory. Nearby there is a large lake, beach, park and shops. Most importantly, there is a tram only three minutes walking away which goes directly to the city centre and central train station in under 15 minutes.

name: Lovely spacious house in the canal belt
summary: Beautiful and complete house, overlooking a charming square in Amsterdam’s famous Canal Belt. Combining scenic views across the Prinsengracht and Amstelveld, on without a doubt one of the most beautiful spots in the centre of Amsterdam, the lodging makes the perfect choice for a family or two couples seeking a memorable Amsterdam adventure. The square in front of the house is a nice playground, ideal for absorbing the sunshine in the warm summer months
space: The authentic characteristics of this 18th century building and detailed interior have been nicely combined, creating a warm and cosy place which will make you feel at home right away. Layout 180 m2 over 3 floors. The stairs in the entrance hall on the ground floor are leading to the first floor with open dining-living room and kitchen looking out over the square and the canal; on the second level there is a separate livingroom with the same view and a study in the back; on the third floor you will find two double bedrooms both with their own bathroom. From here access to the roof terrace with a beautiful view over the city.

neighborhood_overview: This peaceful yet lively area has a lot to offer and creates the perfect opportunity for you to experience Amsterdam as a local. The Utrechtse street and Rembrandt square are just around the corner offering you a very nice selection of bars, local restaurants and trendy shops.  Within 5 minutes walking distance you can find popular places such as the Amstel river, Hermitage Museum and Carré Royal Theatre. The Anne Frank House and museum square, home to Rijksmuseum, Van Gogh museum and Museum of Modern Art, are just a 15-minute stroll away. So is the nine streets area and the oldest part of town around the Nieuwmarkt. The city is easily accessible by tram, bike and boat rental are just around the corner. Closest landmarks     Utrechtsestraat 0.1 km; Museum of Bags and Purses Hendrikje 0.3 km; Skinny bridge 0.3 km; Museum Willet-Holthuysen 0.3 km; Museum van Loon 0.3 km; FOAM Museum of Photography 0.4 km; Carre Theatre 0.4 km; Rembrandtplein 0.4 km; Hermitage Amsterdam 0.5 km; Tuschinski
notes: - Feel free to book if you are a family and/or a small group, but note the maximum is 4 persons, which will be double checked.  - We only accept people who are above 30 years old  or a couple and their children. - Please note that this house is located in a residential area and therefore is not suitable for guests with the intention to party.  - Also note that due to the Dutch architecture style of the building the floors are only accessible through a steep stairway. Therefore, it might not be suitable for guests with reduced mobility
transit: Just 5 minutes walk to public transportation.
access: ★ kitchen equipped with full appliances.  ★ free Wi-Fi (very fast). ★ towels and bedlinnen are provided. ★ Except of the ground floor storage of the owners, you have access to the complete house and you don’t have to share it with others.

name: SUPERBLY LOCATED -MUSEUM SQUARE AT YOUR DOORSTEP
summary: The property lies within 600 meters from Van Gogh Museum.500 m from Museum Square.A variety of cafes and restaurants provide a break from home-cooking, with nearby highlights including the famous steak haven of Loetje, the sublime culinary hotspot of Juuls and the very amazing breakfast joint of Corner Bakery Amsterdam. The  Albert Cuyp Market is accessible on foot in just five minutes and the capital’s focal point of Dam Square can be reached by tram in less than 15 minutes.
space: The apartment is perfectly well equipped, furnished with cable TV with on-demand movies, pay TV, a refrigerator, a kitchen and high ceiling. The studio is beautifully furnished throughout, benefitting from fresh décor, wooden floors, plenty of natural light and stylish fixtures. The central space encourages complete relaxation, supplying a double bed, a flatscreen TV, two vintage armchairs and a fireplace. The double bed can also easily be changed into two single beds.  Nieuw Peking is about 100 meters away and serves Chinese specialties.

summary: Cosy little double bed room.  Located in the very popular De Pijp, known for its designer shops, bars & cosy restaurants. I'd be happy to give you the best tips to discover the great locations and the non touristic Amsterdam...
description: Cosy little double bed room.  Located in the very popular De Pijp, known for its designer shops, bars & cosy restaurants. Albert Cuyp market is 2min walking distance and many trams stop by (15min to Centraal Station). You can relax on our rooftop when the weather allows it! I'd be happy to give you the best tips to discover the great locations and the non touristic Amsterdam... You will access the bedroom, the bathroom/toilets, the rooftop. Some tips in the neighborhood: - Groceries: You have Landmarkt downstairs but it is a bit expensive. You can go to Albert Heijn 3min walk on the left for main groceries. Gall and Gall right  in front of it for the alcohol, Kruidvat for the rest.  - Bikes: You can rent some at the Albert Cuyp Market (careful, it is closed on Sunday).  - ATM : There is one next to the Coffee Company on the corner of Centuurbaan and Van Woustraat + one on the Albert Cuyp market, at the beginning of the street.  - Some nice restaurants : La Spagetheria, The Shanghai Bis
neighborhood_overview: Some tips in the neighborhood: - Groceries: You have Landmarkt downstairs but it is a bit expensive. You can go to Albert Heijn 3min walk on the left for main groceries. Gall and Gall right  in front of it for the alcohol, Kruidvat for the rest.  - Bikes: You can rent some at the Albert Cuyp Market (careful, it is closed on Sunday).  - ATM : There is one next to the Coffee Company on the corner of Centuurbaan and Van Woustraat + one on the Albert Cuyp market, at the beginning of the street.  - Some nice restaurants : La Spagetheria, The Shanghai Bistro, Mana Mana, Yumi Yumi, Mastino Pizza (Not in the neighborhood, but a nice food court: the Food Hallen) - Brunch : Little Collins, Baker and Roosters (need to arrive early), or Esco Bar, Spek - Nice bars : De Tulp, Esco Bar, Glouglou for some wine and cheese
transit: From the airport, take the train to Station RAI. Then you can take the line 4 direction Centraal Station. Stop at Ceintuurbaan (8 stops). The apartment is right there. From Centraal Station you can take the line 4 (on the left when you exit the station). Direction Station RAI, stop at Ceintuurbaan (8 stops). Cross the street in the same direction as the tram and walk for 1min. You will find the apartment on your left side (the door is next to the Landmark supermarket). Down the apartment you can also find the line 3.
access: You will access the bedroom, the bathroom/toilets, the rooftop.

host_about:
Hi, I'm Martijn, 

We are a team of professional hosts established by travelers just like you. We believe in sharing homes. Wherever you are, it is delightful to explore and discover an unknown city from an authentic home. 

On behalf of home owners we advertise their properties through our airbnb profile and support them by offering you a pleasant stay. 

When you book your holiday with us, you can be confident of a memorable stay and an experience through the eyes of a local. We are more than happy to share our knowledge, give you the best insider tips and recommendations about Amsterdam.

If you have any questions, holiday wishes or simply want to have a chat, then feel free to contact us any time. We always reply within an hour!

We look forward to being your host! :)

summary: Our home is a beautiful town house in a very popular neighborhood of Amsterdam (Watergraafsmeer, 10 minutes from the city centre). Our house was built in 1902, it still has many old features, but is also a super cosy and comfortable house. If you're traveling with kids there's also lots of toys you can use. And when you come in summer you can enjoy our lovely veranda and garden with a trampoline in the back for the kids to play on.

name: Trendy design apartment in city centre
summary: Trendy design apartment at central location.Close to the Amstel river, ‘Skinny Bridge’ and Utrechtsestraat the apartment is located central to many of Amsterdam’s sights. The metro and trams stop in front of the door. A variety of restaurants, cafes and shops are around the corner. The city centre as well as the vibrant and upcoming neighborhood East are within walking distance. The apartment is perfect for a couple wanting to explore the city and get a feel of the laid back A'dam way of living.
space: The space The apartment has two floors situated on the first floor and souterain of a traditional Amsterdam building. The living area has a sofa and a nice dining table with cosy bench and streetview. There is an open kitchen, which is fully equipped and there for you to use for that typical Amsterdam breakfast or late night snack. Or just a cup of coffee before going into town.  The souterain contains the master bedroom, a separate toilet, bathroom with rain shower and sunshower (get a tan while you take a shower!) and a nice garden room to relax and read a book. In summer the sunny garden with big dining table and BBQ can be used.

A penalty of €100,- will be charged. * The house is for 4 persons max. No additional guest is allowed to sleep over. * When you are not in the apartment please don't forget to turn off the lights, heating and gaz nozzles; think of the environment. * Lost keys (and those accidentally taken when you have left home) will be replaced for €100,- for replacing the lock and keys.  * Please do not accept any packages from the postman.
host_about:
I am a french man living in Amsterdam for more than 20 years.
At first I came here to work, fell in love and decided to stay. Started a career as a dancer but currently work as a choreographer for different Dutch productions.
In my free time I do yoga, like to travel, cook and visit museums with my friends.
I know Amsterdam and surrounding areas very well. I can advise you the best places to visit, to eat and drink in our area.
And will be delighted to share my knowledge of Amsterdam and the dutchies.
I speak French, English and Dutch and my friend speaks German and some Spanish.

The house has a lot of space and everybody can find its own secret spot to surf on the web, watch tv, read a good novel, relax or simply sleep !! The guests have access to all facilities !! even to the bikes !! Ijburg is born more that 10 years ago from water and sand !! The area is very family oriented with a lot of food shops at the corner. There is a wonderful park (Diemerpark) where you can have a stroll and look at boat traffic on the Amsterdam Rijn Canal. So when you are installed, no need anymore to use your car, bikes and public transport (tram 26 but also bus 66) bring you everywhere in the city without emmiting a gram of CO2 !! The house has a private parking place very close the backyard entry, so coming with a lot of luggages is becoming a pleasure !!

We are a family of 4 persons.. mam, dad and our 2 boys Thomas en Max.
We are a european mix from south/north roots...France and the Netherlands !!
We are very happy to have our house on Airbnb platform because we want to share our cocooning house with people as we do it also with the house of others !!
Sort of sharing house pleasure !!

name: Independent BOATstay at unique SUNNY location
summary: Our spacious INDEPENDENT studio in our new houseboat will provide you an amazing time when visiting Amsterdam. The boat is located in the most romantic neighborhood in the city center. We believe it’s the ultimate location to experience Amsterdam as it is, just outside the touristic area. The studio meets your needs more than expected with a cozy living, a double bed, a private bathroom and a sunny private deck terrace. The ideal retreat if you're looking for something out of the ordinary.
space: This nicely STYLED studio is a perfect getaway. A spacious living with a comfortable double bed with an enormous rooftop window. Ideal for people looking for an unforgettable EXPERIENCE. Have you ever been on a houseboat before? Come and visit ours! Our modern and spacious studio is a great way to stay on a boat. You probably don't want to leave. We do need to alarm you a boat needs special house rules; you get in through a hatch and the sewage system is running on special pumps. So do take these things into account and don't throw any wetties in the toilet... Of course we love to inform you about the do's and the don'ts. The area for sure is the best place to experience Amsterdam... that's if you're not chasing parties  24/7 or hunger for packed touristic streets. The houses in our neighborhood are most wanted and people wo live around here... don't ever want to leave. A village in the center of Amsterdam, with lovely ROMANTIC bridges and a dead ending street to create that ultimate h

You probably don't want to leave. We do need to alarm you a boat needs special house rules; you get in through a hatch and the sewage system is running on special pumps. So do take these thi
neighborhood_overview: The ideal location to spend some valuable time in this wonderfully secluded neighborhood. Loads to do for all tastes, from outdoors adventures for urban city explorers to total isolation for those who prefer the homely and the comfy! We bet you would love to stay on the deck terrace for ever.
notes: Remember: a boat is not a house, please be responsible with our boat systems and its vulnerabilities...If you do throw any wetties or other things in the toilet besides toilet paper, we will have to charge you for the costs to repair, which easily is € 200. Please remind: the boat can rock a bit in strong winds as .. it's a boat. We don't notice it ourselves though, so we can promise: you won't get sea sick.
transit: During the weekend you can park on Westerdok, which is real close for only 12,50 euro each 24 hours. But: you should be out on Monday as it is office parking, please check the website: (Website hidden by Airbnb) so location WESTERDOK. Please do make sure you download the app on forehand and also have an app for paying, such as Yellowbrick. Otherwise you won't get in. It's all on the website of Parkbee. Maybe even make a reservation.  Parking here in the streets is quite expensive about €5 an hour (automatic in many streets, pay with card). But there is this park & ride (P+R) just outside the center where you park your car for about €10 a day, and you get a public transport car within that costs. Then it will take you about 20 minutes to get to our place.  See: (Website hidden by Airbnb) and then pick P+R Sloterdijk and grab bus 48 and get out on stop Barentszplein. Or pick P+R bos and lommer and grab bus 21 and get out on stop Haarlemmerplein. Of course you could also drop your suitcas
interaction: We guarantee an absolutely PRIVATE stay. No sharing, no disturbances. We ourselves live on the same ship, so we'll notice each other on our deck terraces. Also do keep in mind -while the adjacent walls are thick- we might be able to hear each other move about. So let's both respect our relaxation.  I will be very happy to meet your needs during your stay to make your trip to Amsterdam an unforgettable one. We are a family with two little kids so we'll be around much, so don't hesitate to approach one of us if you need anything. From boat trips till restaurant recommendations. Besides that, we’ll leave you to enjoy your stay or.. we can have a drink together on the deck when we both feel like it!
house_rules: - Don't throw anything besides eco toilet paper in the toilet

neighborhood_overview: Amsterdam West is one of the most diverse neighborhoods in town. You'll find almost everything here a from a diversity of coffee places, cool concept stores and vintage boutiques to independent stores and many restaurant hotspots. Amsterdam West is also great for foodies! You'll find a nice eatery at almost every corner. Especially if you enjoy good coffees West is the place to be. The area is close to the city center (7 min by tram) and can be divided in different neighborhoods. All with their own characteristics. Explore them all and discover Amsterdam's first indoor food market ""De Foodhallen"" at Bellamy square. Or go shopping at one of the trendy streets like the Jan Pieter Heijestraat which is packed with cool stores.  When you are more a sportive kind of person you can enjoy a run through the ""Erasmus"" and ""Rembrandtpark"" Our favorite coffee bar is called ""Local Hero"" and is situated on the Jan van Galenstraat. name: Family friendly houseboat central amsterdam
summary: Welcome to our home.  It is a characteristic Amsterdam houseboat, that we have fully refurbished to meet the needs of a family with small children, such as ours. We are located in a quiet corner of the center of Amsterdam. Nevertheless within 1 km. of a wide range of tourist attractions for young and old.  Have a drink on the deck, or run around and feed the swans. This home is made for young and old to enjoy city life outside.  Our private island in the middle of Amsterdam.
space: We live on a historic cargo ship built in 1904. It is fully refurbished and functions a family apartment, with all the comforts of modern life.  Nevertheless you still feel the nautical history of the ship in every detail, from the view through the portholes, to the cascading architecture with small staircases across the boat and the slight rocking of the boat when other ships pass by. We live here with two small children, and have adjusted the ship accordingly, with a fence around the entire ship and adjusted furniture for a toddler (and lots of toys at your disposal). Outside we have spectacular views across the canal, with sun on the bow terrace all day long. Between the ship and the sidewalk we have a flower garden with a second terrace. Shade is provided by the cherry tree and parasol.

neighborhood_overview: We live in the quiet eastern part of the historic centre of Amsterdam. Around the corner you will find boutique shopping (csaar peterstreet area), charming bars and restaurants (world famous Franks Smoke house and brewery 't IJ in the street).  Family destinations like the Maritime museum, Colonial history museum, Nemo (kids' tech lab), and the zoo are all within walking distance.  The neighborhood historically evolved from the docks of Amsterdam, many architectural details still reflect that, including the headquarters of the famous Dutch East India Company (VOC) directly across the street.
notes: Access to the boat and in-house steps can be challenging for people with walking disabilities. Our 2 year-old can run around without problems. We have a cat, Bruno. He will be out when you are here, but if you are heavily allergic please be aware of this. Finally: Living on the water requires no special caution, but some elementary awareness is advised; if you drop your keys, they are really gone..
transit: A bus line (nr 22) takes you to the main train station in 10 minutes, and the tram (10) stops right at our door. The best way to move around the city is obviously by (rental) bike. You can park them right in front of the house.
interaction: When you arrive I will make sure that you are installed comfortably, and hand you any tips and tricks you might want for your stay here.  Should we not be available to welcome you in person, then our neighbor Kees and friend Eva will be there to show you around, and be at your disposal should you have any questions.
host_about:
Hello, we are a social entrepreneur and a doctor living in Amsterdam. On weekdays I divide my time between running my company and a busy schedule as a familyman. With our two children, we live on a lovely houseboat in the center of Amsterdam, which allows us to make plenty of music or go out on the water, when we  have an hour to spare. 

If you don't mind a playful house that's rocking gently,  we would be delighted to have you stay with us,  just like we enjoy staying in inspiring places elsewhere. 

We regularly travel to Paris to visit my family, for which I always aim to stay at nice airbnb places! Maybe yours? In that case: a bientot.
Menno

name: Something different and special
summary: Looking for a very special place to stay in Amsterdam? You’ve found it! Enjoy the sublime view of 4 canals while staying above a famous cafe. The apartment is situated on the 2nd and 3rd floor and located right in the center of Amsterdam. Must sees such as the Anne Frank House, Dam Square and the Jordaan are within walking distance.
space: My house is something very special. It’s very old, authentic and monumental with a lot of stairs, doors and secret corners. I used to get lost a lot in the beginning. Guests are welcome to stay on the second and third floor of this monumental building which is located above one of the oldest cafes of Amsterdam. You’ll have a sublime view over 4 different canals.  The place has two separate bedrooms with 4 beds, a bathroom and small kitchenette on the top floor. The spacious kitchen has all amenities and is located on the second floor. You’ll share the kitchen and the entrance to the second floor with me. My own studio is on the second floor as well and I’m happy to share my (huge) kitchen with you. The third floor (including a small kitchenette) is all yours.

neighborhood_overview: The location of the apartment could not be any better. Amsterdam' must sees such as the Anne Frank House (200m!), Dam Square and the famous 'Jordaan' and '9 little streets' area are all within easy walking distance.  Important to know is that the apartment is located above one of Amsterdam's oldest cafés. This quaint place is loved by many locals and ideal to have drink after a long day in Amsterdam.
notes: Like in most historical canal houses, the stairs are really small and steep. I therefore would urge you not to bring big suitcases as this might be a little problem taking them upstairs.  The kitchen is shared with me, but I'm leaving you all place asked for.  The apartment is located above one of the oldest and nicest cafes in Amsterdam. It’s a popular place for the locals. Especially during the weekends it can be busy and quite noisy.  We occasionally host guests on the first floor of our house, so you might meet other wonderful people on your way in or out.
access: The large kitchen on the second floor.
interaction: I like to make your stay as comfortable as possible. If you like to have a chat and tips about what to do in Amsterdam, I’m happy to inform you. I also respond quickly to your text messages. We share the kitchen and the entrance to the second floor of the apartment. But I will give you as much privacy as you wish.
host_about: Hi! I’m Joris and I like to travel, watch a lot on Netflix, listen to music, skate and meet all kinds of open minded people from all over the world. Together with my sister Anne, we like to host guests in our authentic home and help them to have a great time in Amsterdam.
